#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:473
msgid "Advanced Router Configuration"
msgstr "Configuración Avanzada del Enrutador"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:475
msgid ""
"The router configuration options listed below are not available in the user "
"interface, usually because they are rarely used or provide access to "
"advanced settings that most users will not need. This is not a comprehensive"
" list. Some settings will require a restart of the router to take effect. "
"Note that all settings are case sensitive. You will need to edit your "
"<code>router.config</code> file to add options, or, once you have added "
"<code>routerconsole.advanced=true</code> to the router.config file, you may "
"edit settings within the console on the <a href=/configadvanced>Advanced "
"Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Las opciones de configuración del enrutador enumeradas a continuación no "
"están disponibles en la interfaz de usuario, generalmente porque se usan "
"rara vez o proporcionan acceso a configuraciones avanzadas que la mayoría de"
" usuarios no necesitarán. Esta no es una lista completa. Algunas "
"configuraciones requerirán un reinicio del enrutador para surtir efecto. "
"Tenga en cuenta que todas las configuraciones son sensibles a mayúsculas y "
"minúsculas. Tendrá que editar su archivo <code>router.config</code> para "
"añadir opciones, o, una vez que haya añadido "
"<code>routerconsole.advanced=true</code> al archivo router.config, puede "
"editar las configuraciones dentro de la consola en la página <a "
"href=/configadvanced>Configuración avanzada</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:477
msgid ""
"When set to true, additional functionality will be enabled in the console "
"and the user will be able to edit settings directly on the <a "
"href=/configadvanced>Advanced Configuration page</a>. Extra display options "
"are provided in the <a href=/netdb>Network Database section</a>, including "
"the <a href='/netdb?f=3'>Sybil Analysis tool</a>, and there are additional "
"configuration options on the <a href=/configclients>Clients Configuration "
"page</a>. This will also enable the installation of unsigned updates, manual"
" configuration of the news URL, and additional sections on the sidebar."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, se habilitará funcionalidad adicional en la "
"consola y el usuario podrá editar directamente las configuraciones en la "
"página <a href=/configadvanced>Configuración avanzada</a>. Se proporcionan "
"opciones de visualización adicionales en la sección <a href=/netdb>Base de "
"datos de red</a>, incluida la herramienta de <a href='/netdb?f=3'>Análisis "
"Sybil</a>, y existen opciones de configuración adicionales en la página <a "
"href=/configclients>Configuración de clientes</a>. Esto también permitirá la"
" instalación de actualizaciones no firmadas, la configuración manual de la "
"URL de noticias y secciones adicionales en la barra lateral."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:479
msgid ""
"Plugins signed with the cryptographic key of the developer are the "
"recommended format, but if you wish to install unsigned plugins (.zip) you "
"can set this to true. Note that you may still encounter issues attempting to"
" install an unsigned plugin if the developer has included additional checks "
"in the plugin build process."
msgstr ""
"Los complementos firmados con la clave criptográfica del desarrollador son "
"el formato recomendado, pero si desea instalar complementos no firmados "
"(.zip) puede establecer esto en true. Tenga en cuenta que aún puede "
"encontrarse con problemas al intentar instalar un complemento no firmado si "
"el desarrollador ha incluido comprobaciones adicionales en el proceso de "
"compilación del complemento."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:481
msgid ""
"This setting allows the manual selection of the browser which I2P will "
"launch on startup (if the console is <a "
"href=/configservice#browseronstart>configured</a> to launch a browser on "
"startup), overriding the OS default browser. For more information, see the "
"<a href=#alternative_browser>FAQ entry</a> above."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite la selección manual del navegador que I2P lanzará"
" al inicio (si la consola está <a "
"href=/configservice#browseronstart>configurada</a> para lanzar un navegador "
"al inicio), sobrescribiendo el navegador predeterminado del sistema "
"operativo. Para más información, consultar la entrada de <a "
"href=#alternative_browser>Preguntas frecuentes</a> anterior."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:483
msgid ""
"When set to true, this enables gzip compression for the router console and "
"default web applications. [Enabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, esto habilita la compresión gzip para la "
"consola del enrutador y las aplicaciones web predeterminadas. [Habilitado de"
" forma predeterminada]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:485
msgid ""
"When set to true, this enables plugin installation on the <a "
"href=/configplugins>Plugin Configuration page</a>. [Enabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, esto habilita la instalación de complementos en"
" la página <a href=/configplugins>Configuración de complementos</a>. "
"[Habilitado de forma predeterminada]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:487
msgid ""
"When set to true, this setting enables reverse DNS lookups for peers, "
"triggered when displaying the country flag of a peer or when the hostname or"
" domain is explicitly displayed in the console, or when the peer's "
"RouterInfo is written to disk. In order to avoid repeat lookups, it's "
"recommended to configure a generous caching policy for DNS lookups of 10 "
"minutes or more, and to configure a privacy respecting DNS server in your "
"operating system. [Disabled by default, restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, esta configuración habilita las búsquedas DNS "
"inversas para los pares, activadas al mostrar la bandera del país de un par "
"o al mostrar explícitamente el nombre de host o dominio en la consola, o "
"cuando se escribe en disco la RouterInfo del par. Para evitar búsquedas "
"repetidas, se recomienda configurar una política generosa de caché para las "
"búsquedas DNS de 10 minutos o más, y configurar un servidor DNS respetuoso "
"con la privacidad en tu sistema operativo. [Deshabilitado de forma "
"predeterminada, se requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:489
msgid ""
"This setting permits a custom text prefix to be set for the page title on "
"router console pages, potentially useful when you have multiple consoles "
"open on browser tabs and want an easy method to differentiate between them."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite establecer un prefijo de texto personalizado para"
" el título de la página en las páginas de consola del enrutador, lo cual "
"puede ser útil cuando tienes varias consolas abiertas en pestañas del "
"navegador y quieres un método fácil para diferenciarlas."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:491
msgid ""
"When set to true, accessing the router console via http:// when https:// is "
"enabled will automatically redirect to https. To configure router console "
"access, edit the settings in your <code>clients.config</code> file in your "
"profile directory (<i>not</i> the application installation directory). "
"[Enabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, acceder a la consola del enrutador a través de "
"http:// cuando está habilitado https:// redireccionará automáticamente a "
"https. Para configurar el acceso a la consola del enrutador, edita la "
"configuración en tu archivo <code>clients.config</code> en el directorio de "
"perfil (<i>no</i> el directorio de instalación de la aplicación). "
"[Habilitado de forma predeterminada]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:493
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will display a Peer Test Average readout in "
"the Congestion section of the sidebar, calculated by adding the successful "
"peer test average and the average excess time taken by failed tests. The "
"average value may be used as a guide to determine the optimal "
"<code>router.peerTestTimeout</code> value. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando se establece en true, mostrará una lectura del "
"Promedio de prueba de pares en la sección de Congestión de la barra lateral,"
" calculada sumando el promedio de pruebas exitosas de pares y el tiempo "
"promedio excedido por las pruebas fallidas. El valor promedio puede "
"utilizarse como guía para determinar el valor óptimo de "
"<code>router.peerTestTimeout</code>. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:495
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will display the <i>Sites of Interest</i> "
"links on <a href=/sitemap>the sitemap</a>. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando se establece en true, mostrará los enlaces de "
"<i>Sitios de interés</i> en <a href=/sitemap>el mapa del sitio</a>. "
"[Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:497
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will present the standard sidebar on the "
"homepage, enabling configuration via <a href=/configsidebar>. [Default is "
"false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando se establece en true, presentará la barra lateral"
" estándar en la página de inicio, habilitando configuración vía <a "
"href=/configsidebar>. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:499
msgid ""
"When set to true, the router console will require login authentication. If "
"no password is set, you will be required to set one on the login page. When "
"set to false, the console is accessible without login if no passwords are "
"configured. [Default is false, will be enabled by default in a future "
"release for CSRF defense]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se activa, la consola del router requerira autenticacion de inicio de"
" sesion. Si no se establece contrasena, se te pedira que establezcas una en "
"la pagina de inicio de sesion. Cuando se desactiva, la consola es accesible "
"sin inicio de sesion si no hay contrasenas configuradas. [Por defecto es "
"false, se habilitara por defecto en una version futura para defensa CSRF]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:501
msgid ""
"When set to true, the sidebar bandwidth graph uses the legacy RRD4J SVG "
"renderer. When set to false, the new dual-baseline canvas renderer is used, "
"with gradient fills, glow effects, and a split inbound/outbound display. "
"[Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en verdadero, el gráfico de ancho de banda de la barra "
"lateral usa el motor de renderizado SVG RRD4J heredado. Cuando se establece "
"en falso, se usa el nuevo motor de renderizado de lienzo de doble línea "
"base, con rellenos de degradado, efectos de brillo y una pantalla dividida "
"de entrada/salida. [Predeterminado: falso]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:503
msgid ""
"The time period, in minutes, displayed in the sidebar bandwidth graph. "
"Values outside the valid range (2–30) are clamped. [Default is 20]"
msgstr ""
"El período de tiempo, en minutos, que se muestra en el gráfico de ancho de "
"banda de la barra lateral. Los valores fuera del rango válido (2–30) se "
"limitan. [Predeterminado: 20]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:505
msgid ""
"When set to true (the default), inbound and outbound traffic are displayed "
"in a split view with a center baseline, with outbound spikes upward and "
"inbound spikes downward. When set to false, both lines are displayed in "
"overlay mode from the top of the graph with a configurable composite blend. "
"[Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en verdadero (el predeterminado), el tráfico entrante y "
"saliente se muestra en una vista dividida con una línea base central, con "
"picos salientes hacia arriba y picos entrantes hacia abajo. Cuando se "
"establece en falso, ambas líneas se muestran en modo superpuesto desde la "
"parte superior del gráfico con una mezcla compuesta configurable. "
"[Predeterminado: verdadero]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:507
msgid ""
"Sets the render direction for the sidebar bandwidth graph. When set to rtl "
"(the default), the graph renders right-to-left with newest data on the "
"right. When set to ltr, the graph renders left-to-right with newest data on "
"the left. [Default is rtl]"
msgstr ""
"Establece la dirección de renderizado del gráfico de ancho de banda de la "
"barra lateral. Cuando se establece en rtl (el predeterminado), el gráfico se"
" renderiza de derecha a izquierda con los datos más recientes a la derecha. "
"Cuando se establece en ltr, el gráfico se renderiza de izquierda a derecha "
"con los datos más recientes a la izquierda. [Predeterminado: rtl]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:509
msgid ""
"This setting determines whether or not the router should use the provided "
"<i>blocklist.txt</i> file and any user configured blocklists to enable "
"banning of routers by hash or ip address. Ranges and net masks are supported"
" for IPv4 but not IPv6. See the <i>blocklist.txt</i> in your I2P+ "
"application directory for more info. [Enabled by default, restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina si el enrutador debe usar el archivo "
"<i>blocklist.txt</i> proporcionado y cualquier lista de bloqueo configurada "
"por el usuario para habilitar el bloqueo de enrutadores por hash o dirección"
" IP. Se admiten rangos y máscaras de red para IPv4 pero no para IPv6. "
"Consulta el archivo <i>blocklist.txt</i> en el directorio de tu aplicación "
"I2P+ para más información. [Habilitado de forma predeterminada, se requiere "
"reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:511
msgid ""
"This setting permits an expiry time to be configured (in seconds) for bans "
"enforced via blocklists. By default bans persist for the duration of the "
"router session. [Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite configurar un tiempo de caducidad (en segundos) "
"para los bloqueos impuestos mediante listas de bloqueo. De forma "
"predeterminada, los bloqueos persisten durante la duración de la sesión del "
"enrutador. [Se requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:513
msgid ""
"This setting, when configured with a path pointing at a valid blocklist "
"file, enables an additional, user-configured blocklist to be loaded at "
"router startup. [Disabled by default, restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando se configura con una ruta que apunte a un archivo"
" de lista de bloqueo válido, habilita una lista de bloqueo adicional "
"configurada por el usuario para cargarse en el inicio del enrutador. "
"[Deshabilitado de forma predeterminada, se requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:515
msgid ""
"This setting determines whether or not the router should use the provided "
"<i>blocklist_tor.txt</i> file in your I2P+ application directory to enable "
"banning of routers operating from Tor exit node ip addresses. [Enabled by "
"default, restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina si el enrutador debe usar el archivo "
"<i>blocklist_tor.txt</i> proporcionado en el directorio de tu aplicación "
"I2P+ para habilitar el bloqueo de enrutadores que operen desde direcciones "
"IP de nodos de salida de Tor. [Habilitado de forma predeterminada, se "
"requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:517
msgid ""
"This setting enables requests from routers in the specified countries to be "
"blocked and banned as soon as a direct tunnel request is made. Countries "
"must be specified as two letter country codes, separated with commas. e.g. "
"router.blockCountries=cn,ru"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración habilita que las solicitudes de enrutadores en los países"
" especificados sean bloqueadas y prohibidas tan pronto como se realiza una "
"solicitud de túnel directo. Los países deben especificarse como códigos de "
"país de dos letras, separados por comas. p. ej. router.blockCountries=cn,ru"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:519
msgid ""
"The maximum number of session banlog archive files to keep. When exceeded, "
"older archives are deleted. [Default is 5]"
msgstr ""
"El numero maximo de archivos de archivo de bitacora de baneos de sesion a "
"mantener. Cuando se excede, los archivos mas antiguos se eliminan. [Por "
"defecto es 5]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:521
msgid ""
"The frequency in milliseconds to scan for suspicious hash patterns "
"(potential Sybil attacks). Set to 0 to disable. [Default is 3600000]"
msgstr ""
"La frecuencia en milisegundos para escanear patrones de hash sospechosos "
"(posibles ataques Sybil). Establecer en 0 para deshabilitar. [Por defecto es"
" 3600000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:523
msgid ""
"When set to false, the router will not block tunnel build requests from "
"slower or unreachable routers running older versions. [Default is true, "
"restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en falso, el enrutador no bloqueará las solicitudes de "
"construcción de túneles de enrutadores más lentos o inalcanzables que "
"ejecutan versiones antiguas. [Predeterminado es verdadero, se requiere "
"reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:525
msgid ""
"Allocate number of processor threads for building tunnels. If your processor"
" supports hyperthreading or simultaneous multithreading, you may multiply "
"the number of processor cores by 2 to get the maximum number of threads to "
"allocate, otherwise number of processor cores = maximum number of threads "
"available. Note that you may wish to allocate less than the theoretical "
"maximum to ensure you have headroom for other tasks."
msgstr ""
"Asigna el número de subprocesos del procesador para crear túneles. Si tu "
"procesador admite hyperthreading o multithreading simultáneo, puedes "
"multiplicar el número de núcleos del procesador por 2 para obtener el número"
" máximo de hilos a asignar, de lo contrario el número de núcleos del "
"procesador = número máximo de hilos disponibles. Ten en cuenta que es "
"posible que desees asignar menos que el máximo teórico para asegurarte de "
"tener margen para otras tareas."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:527
msgid ""
"This setting (in milliseconds) determines how long a packet may stay in the "
"CoDel queue before it is dropped. Default is 1000ms. [Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en milisegundos) determina cuánto tiempo puede "
"permanecer un paquete en la cola CoDel antes de ser descartado. "
"Predeterminado es 1000ms. [Reinicio requerido]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:529
msgid ""
"This setting determines the maximum number of messages in the outbound queue"
" before it is marked as full. [Default is 768]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina el número máximo de mensajes en la cola de "
"salida antes de que se marque como llena. [Predeterminado es 768]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:531
msgid ""
"This setting determines the maximum number of messages above the maximum "
"queue value before further messages are dropped. [Default is 128]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina el número máximo de mensajes por encima del "
"valor de cola máximo antes de que se descarten más mensajes. [Predeterminado"
" es 128]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:533
msgid ""
"This setting (in milliseconds) allows you to manually configure the queue "
"delay target value for the CoDel queue management system. Default is 50ms. "
"[Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en milisegundos) te permite configurar manualmente el "
"valor objetivo de retardo de la cola para el sistema de administración de "
"colas CoDel. Predeterminado es 50ms. [Reinicio requerido]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:535
msgid ""
"This setting, in milliseconds, overrides the default message processing time"
" limit (indicated as <i>Message Delay</i> in the Congestion sidebar section)"
" before the router is determined to be congested and transit tunnel requests"
" are rejected. [Default is 750ms or 1500ms if the router is flagged as slow]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, en milisegundos, anula el límite de tiempo "
"predeterminado para el procesamiento de mensajes (indicado como <i>Retardo "
"de mensaje</i> en la sección lateral de Congestión) antes de que se "
"determine que el enrutador está congestionado y se rechacen las solicitudes "
"de túneles de tránsito. [Predeterminado es 750ms o 1500ms si el enrutador "
"está marcado como lento]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:537
msgid ""
"Periodically test tunnels to determine the average lag, and display the "
"results in the Congestion sidepanel section. To enable, set this value to "
"false. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Evaluar periódicamente los túneles para determinar el retardo promedio y "
"mostrar los resultados en la sección lateral de Congestión. Para habilitar, "
"establece este valor en false. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:539
msgid ""
"When set to true, the router will change its identity and UDP port every "
"time the router restarts. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, el enrutador cambiará su identidad y puerto UDP"
" cada vez que se reinicie el enrutador. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:541
msgid ""
"When set to false, the router will not throttle tunnel build requests from "
"other routers, and should be used with caution. [Default is true, restart "
"required]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en falso, el enrutador no limitará las solicitudes de "
"construcción de túneles desde otros enrutadores y debe usarse con "
"precaución. [Predeterminado es verdadero, se requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:543
msgid ""
"This setting determines which <a href=/profiles#profile_defs>peer "
"capabilities</a> will not be used to build your router's tunnels. e.g. "
"<code>router.excludePeerCaps=LMN</code>"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina qué <a href=/profiles#profile_defs>capacidades "
"de par</a> no se usarán para construir los túneles de tu enrutador. Ejemplo:"
" <code>router.excludePeerCaps=LMN</code>"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:545
msgid ""
"When set to false, unreachable peers may be selected as hops for inbound "
"exploratory tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares inaccesibles pueden ser seleccionados como "
"saltos para túneles exploratorios de entrada. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:547
msgid ""
"When set to false, unreachable peers may be selected as hops for outbound "
"exploratory tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares inaccesibles pueden ser seleccionados como "
"saltos para túneles exploratorios de salida. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:549
msgid ""
"When set to false, unreachable peers may be selected as hops for inbound "
"client tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares inaccesibles pueden ser seleccionados como "
"saltos para túneles de cliente de entrada. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:551
msgid ""
"When set to false, unreachable peers may be selected as hops for outbound "
"client tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares inaccesibles pueden ser seleccionados como "
"saltos para túneles de cliente de salida. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:553
msgid ""
"When set to false, slow peers (high tunnel test times) may be selected as "
"hops for inbound exploratory tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares lentos (tiempos de prueba de túnel altos) "
"pueden ser seleccionados como saltos para túneles exploratorios de entrada. "
"[Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:555
msgid ""
"When set to false, slow peers may be selected as hops for outbound "
"exploratory tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares lentos pueden ser seleccionados como saltos "
"para túneles exploratorios de salida. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:557
msgid ""
"When set to false, slow peers may be selected as hops for inbound client "
"tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares lentos pueden ser seleccionados como saltos "
"para túneles de cliente de entrada. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:559
msgid ""
"When set to false, slow peers may be selected as hops for outbound client "
"tunnels. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se desactiva, los pares lentos pueden ser seleccionados como saltos "
"para túneles de cliente de salida. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:561
msgid ""
"This setting (in hours) determines how old a RouterInfo in the NetDb is (its"
" last known publication date) before it's classified as stale and deleted. "
"[Default is 28 hours unless the router is a Floodfill, in which case the "
"default is 8 hours]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en horas) determina cuán antigua es una RouterInfo en el"
" NetDb (su última fecha de publicación conocida) antes de que se clasifique "
"como obsoleta y se elimine. [Predeterminado son 28 horas a menos que el "
"enrutador sea un punto de inundación, en cuyo caso el predeterminado son 8 "
"horas]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:563
msgid ""
"This setting determines the number of peers to explore in parallel when the "
"Peer Exploration Job runs [default is 1 peer at a time when more than 3000 "
"peers are known]. Note that increasing this value will increase the "
"bandwidth requirements for the exploration, and setting this value too high "
"may cause excessive message delay and interfere with other services, so use "
"with caution!"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina el número de pares que se explorarán en "
"paralelo cuando se ejecuta el Trabajo de exploración de pares "
"[predeterminado es 1 par cada vez cuando se conocen más de 3000 pares]. Ten "
"en cuenta que aumentar este valor aumentará los requisitos de ancho de banda"
" para la exploración, y establecer este valor demasiado alto puede causar "
"retrasos excesivos de mensajes e interferir con otros servicios, ¡ten "
"cuidado!"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:565
msgid ""
"This setting determines the number of NetDb DHT buckets the Peer Exploration"
" Job will reference when run. By default, the number of buckets to explore "
"will vary depending on whether the router has been running for over an hour,"
" if the router is hidden or in the 'K' bandwidth tier, and the number of "
"known routers."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina la cantidad de cubos DHT de NetDb a los que se "
"hará referencia cuando se ejecute el Trabajo de exploración de pares. De "
"forma predeterminada, la cantidad de cubos a explorar variará en función de "
"si el enrutador lleva más de una hora funcionando, si el enrutador está "
"oculto o en la categoría de ancho de banda 'K', y la cantidad de enrutadores"
" conocidos."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:567
msgid ""
"This setting (in seconds) allows you to override the delay between runs of "
"the Peer Exploration Job which attempts to locate new peers to add to the "
"NetDb. The job will run every 80 seconds by default, or if the router is "
"experiencing job or message lag, every 3 minutes. If the size of the NetDb "
"reaches 4000 peers, the pause will increase to 15 minutes. You may wish to "
"increase the delay if your NetDb is well-populated (over 2000 peers), or if "
"you wish to reduce overall bandwidth usage. Note: For Floodfill routers, "
"this job does not run."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en segundos) te permite anular el retardo entre "
"ejecuciones del Trabajo de exploración de pares que intenta localizar nuevos"
" pares para agregar a NetDb. El trabajo se ejecutará cada 80 segundos de "
"forma predeterminada, o si el enrutador experimenta retrasos en trabajos o "
"mensajes, cada 3 minutos. Si el tamaño de NetDb alcanza 4000 pares, la pausa"
" aumentará a 15 minutos. Puede que desees aumentar el retardo si tu NetDb "
"tiene muchos contactos (más de 2000 pares), o si deseas reducir el uso "
"general de ancho de banda. Nota: Para los enrutadores punto de inundación, "
"este trabajo no se ejecuta."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:569
msgid ""
"This setting determines the maximum number of peer hashes to queue for "
"exploration. In I2P the maximum is 128, and in I2P+ the default value is "
"512."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina el número máximo de hashes de pares para "
"encolar para la exploración. En I2P el máximo es 128, y en I2P+ el valor "
"predeterminado es 512."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:571
msgid ""
"This setting determines whether a router acting as a floodfill will explore "
"the NetDb to learn about new peers. [Default is false, restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina si un enrutador que actúa como punto de "
"inundación explorará NetDb para conocer nuevos pares. [Predeterminado es "
"false, se requiere reinicio]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:573
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, prevents a router from directly "
"communicating with other routers, forcing the use of introducers. [Default "
"is false unlesss router is in hidden mode]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando se establece en true, evita que un enrutador se "
"comunique directamente con otros enrutadores, forzando el uso de "
"presentadores. [El predeterminado es false a menos que el enrutador esté en "
"modo oculto]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:575
msgid ""
"When set to true, if your router is serving as a floodfill for the network, "
"your <a href=/configadvanced#ffconf>floodfill participation</a> will be "
"hidden from other routers."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, si tu enrutador está sirviendo como punto de "
"inundación para la red, tu <a href=/configadvanced#ffconf>participación como"
" punto de inundación</a> se ocultará a otros enrutadores."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:577
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum number of parallel <a href=/jobs>jobs</a> that can be "
"run. The default value is determined by the amount of memory allocated to "
"the JVM via <code>wrapper.config</code>, and is set at 3 for less than 64MB,"
" 4 for less than 256M, or 5 for more than 256MB. Note: A change to this "
"setting requires a restart of the router."
msgstr ""
"Define el número máximo de <a href=/jobs>tareas</a> paralelas que se pueden "
"ejecutar. El valor predeterminado se determina por la cantidad de memoria "
"asignada a la JVM a través de <code>wrapper.config</code>, y se establece en"
" 3 para menos de 64MB, 4 para menos de 256M o 5 para más de 256MB. Nota: Un "
"cambio en esta configuración requiere reiniciar el enrutador."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:579
msgid ""
"Defines the minimum number of parallel <a href=/jobs>job runners</a>. The "
"router will not scale down below this number. Default is 4, minimum is 1. "
"This setting is dynamic and takes effect without restart."
msgstr ""
"Define el numero minimo de <a href=/jobs>ejecutores de trabajos</a> "
"paralelos. El router no reducira por debajo de este numero. Por defecto es "
"4, minimo es 1. Esta configuracion es dinamica y surte efecto sin reinicio."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:581
msgid ""
"Enable dynamic scaling of job runners based on queue load. When enabled, the"
" router automatically scales the number of job runner threads up or down "
"based on ready job count and lag. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Habilitar escalado dinamico de ejecutores de trabajos basado en la carga de "
"la cola. Cuando esta activado, el router escala automaticamente el numero de"
" hilos ejecutores segun la cantidad de trabajos listos y el retraso. [Por "
"defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:583
msgid ""
"The job queue lag threshold in milliseconds that triggers scaling up job "
"runners. When max lag exceeds this value, additional runners are started. "
"[Default is 1]"
msgstr ""
"El umbral de retraso de la cola de trabajos en milisegundos que activa el "
"escalado de ejecutores. Cuando el retraso maximo supera este valor, se "
"inician ejecutores adicionales. [Por defecto es 1]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:585
msgid ""
"The job queue lag threshold in milliseconds that allows scaling down job "
"runners. When max lag stays below this value, excess runners are stopped. "
"[Default is 1]"
msgstr ""
"El umbral de retraso de la cola de trabajos en milisegundos que permite "
"reducir los ejecutores. Cuando el retraso maximo se mantiene por debajo de "
"este valor, los ejecutores sobrantes se detienen. [Por defecto es 1]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:587
msgid ""
"The ratio of ready jobs to active runners that triggers scaling up. If "
"readyJobs > activeRunners * ratio, additional runners are started. [Default "
"is 1.2]"
msgstr ""
"La proporcion de trabajos listos a ejecutores activos que activa el "
"escalado. Si trabajosListos > ejecutoresActivos * proporcion, se inician "
"ejecutores adicionales. [Por defecto es 1.2]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:589
msgid ""
"The interval in milliseconds between job runner scaling checks. [Default is "
"1000]"
msgstr ""
"El intervalo en milisegundos entre verificaciones de escalado de ejecutores."
" [Por defecto es 1000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:591
msgid ""
"The cooldown period in milliseconds between scale operations. [Default is "
"5000]"
msgstr ""
"El periodo de enfriamiento en milisegundos entre operaciones de escalado. "
"[Por defecto es 5000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:593
msgid ""
"Enable the feedback mechanism that automatically rolls back ineffective "
"scale-up operations. If lag increases after adding runners, they will be "
"removed. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Habilitar el mecanismo de retroalimentacion que revierte automaticamente las"
" operaciones de escalado ineficaces. Si el retraso aumenta despues de anadir"
" ejecutores, se eliminaran. [Por defecto es true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:595
msgid ""
"The maximum number of waiting jobs in the queue before aggressive job "
"dropping is triggered. When exceeded, non-critical jobs are dropped to "
"reduce queue pressure. [Default is 48]"
msgstr ""
"El numero maximo de trabajos en espera en la cola antes de activar el "
"descarte agresivo de trabajos. Cuando se supera, los trabajos no criticos se"
" descartan para reducir la presion de la cola. [Por defecto es 48]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:597
msgid ""
"Maximum number of pending tunnel build jobs in the BuildHandler queue. When "
"the queue exceeds this limit, new build requests are rejected to prevent job"
" queue overload. [Default is 256]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de trabajos de construccion de túnel pendientes en la cola de "
"BuildHandler. Cuando la cola supera este limite, las nuevas solicitudes de "
"construccion se rechazan para evitar la sobrecarga de la cola. [Por defecto "
"es 256]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:599
msgid ""
"Multiplier applied to the base tunnel build concurrency. The effective "
"concurrency is baseBuildRate * multiplier, clamped by maxConcurrentBuilds. "
"Higher values accelerate pool recovery but increase network load. [Default "
"is 1.0]"
msgstr ""
"Multiplicador aplicado a la concurrencia base de construccion de túneles. La"
" concurrencia efectiva es baseBuildRate * multiplicador, limitada por "
"maxConcurrentBuilds. Valores mas altos aceleran la recuperacion del grupo "
"pero aumentan la carga de la red. [Por defecto es 1.0]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:601
msgid ""
"Determines the maximum number of participating tunnels the router can build."
" To disable participation completely, set to 0. [Default is 8000, or 2000 if"
" running on Arm or Android]"
msgstr ""
"Determina el número máximo de túneles participativos que puede construir el "
"enrutador. Para deshabilitar la participación completamente, establece en 0."
" [Predeterminado es 8000, o 2000 si se ejecuta en Arm o Android]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:603
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum percentage of active local tunnels (client and "
"exploratory) that a peer will be used for. [Default is 10% in I2P+, 33% in "
"I2P]"
msgstr ""
"Define el porcentaje máximo de túneles locales activos (cliente y "
"exploratorios) para los que se usará un par. [Predeterminado es 10% en I2P+,"
" 33% en I2P]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:605
msgid ""
"This setting allows you to configure the minimum number of hosted "
"participating tunnels before the router starts to reject tunnel requests "
"based on anticipated bandwidth requirements. [Default is 100 if system is "
"running Android, 800 if system is running on ARM and less than 4 cores "
"available, 1200 if system is running on ARM and 4 or more cores available, "
"otherwise 2500]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración te permite establecer el número mínimo de túneles "
"participativos alojados antes de que el enrutador empiece a rechazar "
"solicitudes de túnel en función de los requisitos de ancho de banda "
"anticipados. [Predeterminado es 100 si el sistema está ejecutando Android, "
"800 si el sistema está ejecutando ARM y menos de 4 núcleos disponibles, 1200"
" si el sistema está ejecutando ARM y 4 o más núcleos disponibles, de lo "
"contrario 2500]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:607
msgid ""
"This setting allows you to exclude older routers from your NetDb. Routers "
"older than the default or the value you set will be deleted from the NetDb "
"and banned for the duration of the router session. By default, routers older"
" than 0.9.20 are excluded. Note: starting with I2P+ version 0.9.46+, only "
"routers running very recent versions are used for building local tunnels. "
"[Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración te permite excluir enrutadores más antiguos de tu NetDb. "
"Los enrutadores más antiguos que el predeterminado o el valor que "
"establezcas se eliminarán de NetDb y se prohibirán durante la sesión del "
"enrutador. De forma predeterminada, se excluyen los enrutadores más antiguos"
" que la versión 0.9.20. Nota: a partir de la versión I2P+ 0.9.46+, solo se "
"usan enrutadores con versiones muy recientes para construir túneles locales."
" [Reinicio requerido]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:609
msgid ""
"When set to true, the router info files stored in your profile's netDB "
"directory will not be split into 64 sub-directories. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, los archivos de información del enrutador "
"almacenados en el directorio netDB de tu perfil no se dividirán en 64 "
"subdirectorios. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:611
msgid ""
"When set to true, your router will not be classified as slow, regardless of "
"the specifications of your host system. Ordinarily, routers running on hosts"
" with the following characteristics will be classified as slow, and various "
"performance-related router options will be modified accordingly:"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, tu enrutador no se clasificará como lento, "
"independientemente de las especificaciones de tu sistema anfitrión. "
"Normalmente, los enrutadores que se ejecutan en anfitriones con las "
"siguientes características se clasificarán como lentos, y se modificarán "
"varias opciones relacionadas con el rendimiento del enrutador en "
"consecuencia:"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:613
msgid "Host OS running Android"
msgstr "Sistema operativo anfitrión ejecutando Android"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:615
msgid "Host OS running on ARM (MacOS excepted)"
msgstr "Sistema operativo anfitrión ejecutándose en ARM (excepto MacOS)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:617
msgid "32bit host OS running with less than 4 detected cores"
msgstr ""
"Sistema operativo anfitrión de 32 bits ejecutándose con menos de 4 núcleos "
"detectados"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:619
msgid ""
"64bit host OS running with 1 detected core and less than 384MB allocated to "
"the JVM"
msgstr ""
"Sistema operativo anfitrión de 64 bits ejecutándose con 1 núcleo detectado y"
" menos de 384MB asignados a la JVM"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:621
msgid "Less than 256MB allocated to the JVM"
msgstr "Menos de 256MB asignados a la JVM"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:623
msgid ""
"Router running a non-native, software emulated version of the Java "
"BigInteger library"
msgstr ""
"Enrutador ejecutando una versión emulada por software, no nativa, de la "
"biblioteca Java BigInteger"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:625
msgid ""
"This setting determines the number of peer tests to run concurrently, used "
"to determine peer latency. When tunnel build success drops below 50%, "
"concurrency is halved to avoid adding load during a failure cascade. "
"[Default varies: 1 on slow systems, 2 on single/dual-core, 4 otherwise]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuracion determina el numero de pruebas de par a ejecutar "
"concurrentemente, utilizadas para determinar la latencia del par. Cuando el "
"exito de construccion de túnel cae por debajo del 50%, la concurrencia se "
"reduce a la mitad para evitar anadir carga durante una cascada de fallos. "
"[El valor por defecto varia: 1 en sistemas lentos, 2 en mononúcleo/dual-"
"núcleo, 4 en otros casos]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:627
msgid ""
"This setting determines the delay between peer test jobs, configured in "
"milliseconds. [Default is 30000 (30s), or 45000 (45s) on slow systems]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuracion determina el retraso entre trabajos de prueba de par, en "
"milisegundos. [Por defecto es 30000 (30s), o 45000 (45s) en sistemas lentos]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:629
msgid ""
"To determine peer latency, this setting allocates the maximum time a peer "
"test should take before being considered a failure, configured in "
"milliseconds. In the event that the timeout is configured lower than the "
"average successful test, the average successful test value will be used. "
"[Default is 5000]"
msgstr ""
"Para determinar la latencia del par, esta configuracion asigna el tiempo "
"maximo que una prueba de par debe tomar antes de considerarse un fallo, en "
"milisegundos. Si el tiempo de espera se configura por debajo del valor medio"
" de pruebas exitosas, se usara el valor medio de pruebas exitosas. [Por "
"defecto es 5000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:631
msgid ""
"Minimum number of peers to retain in the fast tier during profile "
"reorganization. A higher value ensures more peers are available for tunnel "
"building, at the cost of potentially including slower peers. If more than "
"3000 routers are known, the default scales to <code>knownRouters / "
"15</code>. [Default is 400]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de pares a retener en el nivel rapido durante la "
"reorganizacion de perfiles. Un valor mas alto asegura que mas pares esten "
"disponibles para la construccion de túneles, a costa de incluir "
"potencialmente pares mas lentos. Si se conocen mas de 3000 routers, el valor"
" por defecto escala a <code>knownRouters / 15</code>. [Por defecto es 400]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:633
msgid ""
"Minimum number of peers to retain in the high-capacity tier. These are the "
"peers with the highest measured throughput and greatest ability to relay "
"traffic. If more than 3000 routers are known, the default scales to "
"<code>knownRouters / 15</code>. [Default is 500]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de pares a retener en el nivel de alta capacidad. Estos son "
"los pares con el mayor rendimiento medido y mayor capacidad para "
"retransmitir trafico. Si se conocen mas de 3000 routers, el valor por "
"defecto escala a <code>knownRouters / 15</code>. [Por defecto es 500]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:635
msgid ""
"Maximum number of peer profiles to retain in memory. Older, inactive "
"profiles are expired first when this limit is reached. Values below 100 are "
"clamped to 100. [Default is 8000, or 800 on slow systems]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de perfiles de par a retener en memoria. Los perfiles mas "
"antiguos e inactivos se eliminan primero cuando se alcanza este limite. "
"Valores por debajo de 100 se ajustan a 100. [Por defecto es 8000, o 800 en "
"sistemas lentos]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:637
msgid ""
"Maximum age of a RouterInfo (in hours) for a peer to be considered "
"selectable for tunnel building. Peers with RouterInfos older than this "
"threshold are excluded from selection unless they have an active connection."
" This is particularly relevant for floodfill routers that do not actively "
"explore the NetDB, as their RouterInfos may become stale without periodic "
"refresh. [Default is 3]"
msgstr ""
"Edad maxima de una RouterInfo (en horas) para que un par sea considerado "
"seleccionable para construccion de túnel. Los pares con RouterInfos mas "
"antiguas que este umbral son excluidos de la seleccion a menos que tengan "
"una conexion activa. Esto es particularmente relevante para routers "
"floodfill que no exploran activamente la NetDB, ya que sus RouterInfos "
"pueden quedar obsoletas sin actualizacion periodica. [Por defecto es 3]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:639
msgid ""
"This setting determines whether stats about our router are sporadically "
"published to the NetDb. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina si las estadísticas de nuestro enrutador se "
"publican esporádicamente en NetDb. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:641
msgid ""
"This setting configures the initial size of the outbound message queue. "
"[Default is 64]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración establece el tamaño inicial de la cola de mensajes "
"salientes. [Predeterminado es 64]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:643
msgid ""
"This setting configures the maximum number of inbound messages queued per "
"cycle (pump). [Default is 24]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración establece el número máximo de mensajes entrantes "
"encolados por ciclo (bombeo). [Predeterminado es 24]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:645
msgid ""
"This setting configures the maximum size of the inbound message queue. "
"[Default is 1024]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración establece el tamaño máximo de la cola de mensajes "
"entrantes. [Predeterminado es 1024]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:647
msgid ""
"This setting configures the maximum number of outbound messages queued per "
"cycle (pump). [Default is 64]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración establece el número máximo de mensajes salientes "
"encolados por ciclo (bombeo). [Predeterminado es 64]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:649
msgid ""
"When set to true, the router will change its identity and UDP port when the "
"router restarts and then delete the key from router.config to prevent "
"further changes. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, el enrutador cambiará su identidad y puerto UDP"
" cuando se reinicie el enrutador y luego eliminará la clave de router.config"
" para evitar más cambios. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:651
msgid ""
"This setting (in milliseconds) allows you to manually configure the delay "
"between router refresh updates run by the Refresh Routers Job. By default "
"the pause between refreshes is determined by the size of the NetDb, and "
"introduces some randomness in the timing to mitigate traffic analysis. For "
"values lower than 2000 milliseconds, increasing the value of "
"<code>router.refreshTimeout</code> is recommended. Note that setting this "
"value below 2000 milliseconds will increase your network traffic and may "
"introduce job lag, and is not recommended for sustained use."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en milisegundos) le permite configurar manualmente el "
"retardo entre las actualizaciones de actualización de enrutadores ejecutadas"
" por el Trabajo de actualización de enrutadores. De forma predeterminada, la"
" pausa entre actualizaciones se determina según el tamaño de NetDb e "
"introduce cierta aleatoriedad en la programación para mitigar el análisis de"
" tráfico. Para valores inferiores a 2000 milisegundos, se recomienda "
"aumentar el valor de <code>router.refreshTimeout</code>. Ten en cuenta que "
"establecer este valor por debajo de 2000 milisegundos aumentará su tráfico "
"de red y puede introducir retrasos en trabajos, y no se recomienda para uso "
"continuado."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:653
msgid ""
"This setting (in hours) allows you to manually configure how old a "
"RouterInfo is in order for it to be checked by the Refresh Routers Job. By "
"default, the age of a RouterInfo before a refresh is intitiated scales "
"according to the size of the NetDb, increasing as the NetDb grows in size. A"
" value of 0 will force the Router Refresh Job to check every router in the "
"NetDb, regardless of age."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en horas) le permite configurar manualmente con qué "
"antigüedad debe tener una RouterInfo para que sea revisada por el Trabajo de"
" actualización de enrutadores. De forma predeterminada, la antigüedad de una"
" RouterInfo antes de iniciar una actualización escala según el tamaño de "
"NetDb, aumentando a medida que crece NetDb. Un valor de 0 obligará al "
"Trabajo de actualización de enrutadores a revisar cada enrutador en NetDb, "
"independientemente de su antigüedad."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:655
msgid ""
"This setting (in seconds) allows you to manually configure the amount of "
"time to wait before an attempt to refresh a router is determined to have "
"failed. [The default is 20 seconds]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en segundos) le permite configurar manualmente la "
"cantidad de tiempo que debe esperarse antes de que se determine que un "
"intento de actualización de un enrutador ha fallado. [El predeterminado son "
"20 segundos]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:657
msgid ""
"This setting determines whether routers classified as uninteresting (K or L "
"tier, unreachable or older than 0.9.50) are checked during the refresh "
"router process after 1 hour of uptime. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina si los enrutadores clasificados como poco "
"interesantes (nivel K o L, inalcanzables o más antiguos que la versión "
"0.9.50) se revisan durante el proceso de actualización del enrutador después"
" de 1 hora de funcionamiento. [Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:659
msgid ""
"When set to true, this setting will relax the conditions required for your "
"router to publish congestion caps, specifically when it's determined that "
"your bandwidth usage is high. Other conditions, such as high job lag or a "
"router classified as slow, will still cause caps to be published. [Default "
"is false]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, esta configuración relajará las condiciones "
"requeridas para que su enrutador publique límites de congestión, "
"específicamente cuando se determina que su uso de ancho de banda es alto. "
"Otras condiciones, como alta latencia de trabajo o un enrutador clasificado "
"como lento, seguirán causando que se publiquen límites. [Predeterminado es "
"false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:661
msgid ""
"When configured, this sets a hard limit for the number of tunnels the router"
" is permitted to build concurrently. By default the router uses the average "
"build time and current outbound bandwidth to determine the optimum build "
"rate. This setting is dynamic and takes effect without restart."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se configura, establece un limite estricto para el numero de túneles "
"que el router puede construir concurrentemente. Por defecto, el router usa "
"el tiempo medio de construccion y el ancho de banda de salida actual para "
"determinar la tasa optima de construccion. Esta configuracion es dinamica y "
"surte efecto sin reinicio."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:663
msgid ""
"When set to true, the router uses the older peer selection algorithm when "
"building tunnels (prefer fast peers directly, without the multi-tier HighCap"
" → Fast → Active fallback chain). May be useful for troubleshooting peer "
"selection issues. [Default is false. This setting is dynamic and takes "
"effect immediately.]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se activa, el router usa el algoritmo de seleccion de pares mas "
"antiguo al construir túneles (preferir pares rapidos directamente, sin la "
"cadena de respaldo multi-nivel HighCap → Fast → Active). Puede ser útil para"
" solucionar problemas de seleccion de pares. [Por defecto es false. Esta "
"configuracion es dinamica y surte efecto inmediatamente.]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:665
msgid ""
"Growth factor used by the router's transit tunnel throttle. Higher values "
"make the router accept tunnel build requests more aggressively relative to "
"the 10-minute average. Lower values make it probabalistically reject sooner "
"when tunnel counts are rising rapidly. [Default is 2.0]"
msgstr ""
"Factor de crecimiento utilizado por el regulador de túneles de transito del "
"router. Valores mas altos hacen que el router acepte solicitudes de "
"construccion de túnel de forma mas agresiva en relacion con la media de 10 "
"minutos. Valores mas bajos hacen que rechace de forma probabilistica antes "
"cuando los recuentos de túneles aumentan rapidamente. [Por defecto es 2.0]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:667
msgid ""
"Growth factor for tunnel test time acceptance rate limiting. If the 1-minute"
" average test time exceeds the 1-hour average multiplied by this factor, the"
" router begins probabalistically rejecting. [Default is 1.5]"
msgstr ""
"Factor de crecimiento para la limitacion de la tasa de aceptacion de tiempo "
"de prueba de túnel. Si el tiempo medio de prueba de 1 minuto supera la media"
" de 1 hora multiplicada por este factor, el router comienza a rechazar "
"probabilisticamente. [Por defecto es 1.5]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:669
msgid ""
"Controls the steepness of the rejection probability curve when bandwidth "
"usage approaches capacity. Lower values give a smoother transition (less "
"aggressive rejection at moderate load). [Default is 10]"
msgstr ""
"Controla la pendiente de la curva de probabilidad de rechazo cuando el uso "
"del ancho de banda se acerca a la capacidad. Valores mas bajos dan una "
"transicion mas suave (rechazo menos agresivo con carga moderada). [Por "
"defecto es 10]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:671
msgid ""
"Penalty multiplier applied to a peer's capacity value when the peer "
"publishes a 'D' congestion cap (moderate congestion). Higher values reduce "
"the peer's effective capacity more aggressively. [Default is 2.5]"
msgstr ""
"Multiplicador de penalizacion aplicado al valor de capacidad de un par "
"cuando el par publica un limite de congestion 'D' (congestion moderada). "
"Valores mas altos reducen la capacidad efectiva del par de forma mas "
"agresiva. [Por defecto es 2.5]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:673
msgid ""
"Penalty multiplier applied to a peer's capacity value when the peer "
"publishes an 'E' congestion cap (severe congestion). [Default is 4.75]"
msgstr ""
"Multiplicador de penalizacion aplicado al valor de capacidad de un par "
"cuando el par publica un limite de congestion 'E' (congestion severa). [Por "
"defecto es 4.75]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:675
msgid ""
"Time in milliseconds before expiration when pruned tunnels are marked for "
"early expiry, giving replacement tunnels time to build. Higher values allow "
"more overlap between old and new tunnels. [Default is 120000 (2 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo en milisegundos antes de la caducidad cuando los túneles podados se "
"marcan para caducidad anticipada, dando tiempo a los túneles de reemplazo "
"para construirse. Valores mas altos permiten mas superposicion entre túneles"
" viejos y nuevos. [Por defecto es 120000 (2 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:677
msgid ""
"The latency threshold in milliseconds for removing slow tunnels from <a "
"href=/tunnels>local tunnel pools</a>. Tunnels with latency above this "
"threshold will be removed if the pool exceeds the minimum tunnel count. Set "
"to 0 to use 1 second or the lowest recorded latency from all pools, "
"whichever is higher. [Default is 0]"
msgstr ""
"El umbral de latencia en milisegundos para eliminar túneles lentos de los <a"
" href=/tunnels>grupos de túneles locales</a>. Los túneles con latencia "
"superior a este umbral se eliminaran si el grupo supera el numero minimo de "
"túneles. Establecer en 0 para usar 1 segundo o la latencia mas baja "
"registrada de todos los grupos, la que sea mayor. [Por defecto es 0]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:679
msgid ""
"The minimum number of tunnels to keep in each pool when removing slow "
"tunnels (minimum 2), overriding the configured tunnel quantity. Set to 0 to "
"use the configured quantity per pool. [Default is 0]"
msgstr ""
"El numero minimo de túneles a mantener en cada grupo al eliminar túneles "
"lentos (minimo 2), anulando la cantidad configurada de túneles. Establecer "
"en 0 para usar la cantidad configurada por grupo. [Por defecto es 0]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:681
msgid ""
"The interval in milliseconds between runs of the Remove Slow Tunnels job. "
"Higher values reduce tunnel churn but may keep slow tunnels longer. [Default"
" is 90000 (90s), or 120000 (120s) if under load]"
msgstr ""
"El intervalo en milisegundos entre ejecuciones del trabajo de Eliminacion de"
" Túneles Lentos. Valores mas altos reducen la rotacion de túneles pero "
"pueden mantener túneles lentos por mas tiempo. [Por defecto es 90000 (90s), "
"o 120000 (120s) si está bajo carga]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:683
msgid ""
"The time in milliseconds before expiration to mark tunnels for early expiry "
"when the Remove Slow Tunnels job prunes slow or excess tunnels. Higher "
"values allow more time for new tunnels to build. [Default is 30000]"
msgstr ""
"El tiempo en milisegundos antes de la caducidad para marcar túneles para "
"caducidad anticipada cuando el trabajo de Eliminacion de Túneles Lentos poda"
" túneles lentos o excedentes. Valores mas altos permiten mas tiempo para "
"construir nuevos túneles. [Por defecto es 30000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:685
msgid ""
"Hard limit on total tunnel test jobs (queued + active). Prevents runaway "
"test backlogs from causing job queue lag. Once reached, no new tests are "
"scheduled until the count drops. [Default is 128 (96 on slower systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Limite estricto en total de trabajos de prueba de túnel (en cola + activos)."
" Evita que los retrasos de pruebas descontrolados causen retraso en la cola "
"de trabajos. Una vez alcanzado, no se programan nuevas pruebas hasta que el "
"recuento baje. [Por defecto es 128 (96 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:687
msgid ""
"Base adaptive queue limit for tunnel test jobs. The router scales this "
"up/down by 2-3x based on job queue lag and failure rates. [Default is 48 (32"
" on slower systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Limite de cola adaptativo base para trabajos de prueba de túnel. El router "
"escala esto hacia arriba/abajo por 2-3x basándose en el retraso de la cola y"
" las tasas de fallo. [Por defecto es 48 (32 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:689
msgid ""
"Maximum number of tunnel tests that can execute simultaneously. Caps "
"concurrent test throughput to prevent overwhelming the router. [Default is "
"64 (32 on slower systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de pruebas de túnel que pueden ejecutarse simultaneamente. "
"Limita el rendimiento concurrente de pruebas para evitar sobrecargar el "
"router. [Por defecto es 64 (32 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:691
msgid ""
"Maximum consecutive client tunnel build timeouts before forcing exploratory "
"tunnels for build reply delivery. Higher values keep the router trying "
"paired tunnels longer; lower values fall back to exploratory sooner. "
"[Default is 3]"
msgstr ""
"Maximo de tiempos de espera consecutivos de construccion de túnel de cliente"
" antes de forzar túneles exploratorios para la entrega de respuestas de "
"construccion. Valores mas altos mantienen el router intentando túneles "
"emparejados por mas tiempo; valores mas bajos recurren a exploratorios "
"antes. [Por defecto es 3]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:693
msgid ""
"How long to wait for a tunnel build reply before trying a different pool or "
"different peers. The BuildExecutor adaptively increases this when success "
"rates are low. [Default is 5000 (5s), 10000 (10s) on slow systems]"
msgstr ""
"Cuanto tiempo esperar una respuesta de construccion de túnel antes de probar"
" un grupo diferente o pares diferentes. El BuildExecutor aumenta esto "
"adaptativamente cuando las tasas de exito son bajas. [Por defecto es 5000 "
"(5s), 10000 (10s) en sistemas lentos]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:695
msgid ""
"Timeout in milliseconds for the first-hop OutNetMessage before firing "
"TunnelBuildFirstHopFailJob. Should be >= requestTimeout for proper "
"sequencing. [Default is 10000 (10 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo de espera en milisegundos para el OutNetMessage de primer salto antes"
" de activar TunnelBuildFirstHopFailJob. Debe ser >= requestTimeout para una "
"secuenciacion adecuada. [Por defecto es 10000 (10 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:697
msgid ""
"Timeout in milliseconds for RouterInfo lookup of the next hop during tunnel "
"build processing. If the lookup times out, the build request is rejected. "
"[Default is 8000 (8 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo de espera en milisegundos para la busqueda de RouterInfo del "
"siguiente salto durante el procesamiento de construccion de túnel. Si la "
"busqueda expira, la solicitud de construccion se rechaza. [Por defecto es "
"8000 (8 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:699
msgid ""
"Backoff delay in milliseconds between exploratory tunnel build retries. "
"Higher values reduce build request rate during failures; lower values retry "
"faster. [Default is 200]"
msgstr ""
"Retraso de retroceso en milisegundos entre reintentos de construccion de "
"túnel exploratorio. Valores mas altos reducen la tasa de solicitudes de "
"construccion durante fallos; valores mas bajos reintentan mas rapido. [Por "
"defecto es 200]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:701
msgid ""
"Backoff delay in milliseconds between client tunnel build retries. Lower "
"values rebuild failed client tunnels faster. [Default is 50]"
msgstr ""
"Retraso de retroceso en milisegundos entre reintentos de construccion de "
"túnel de cliente. Valores mas bajos reconstruyen túneles de cliente fallidos"
" mas rapido. [Por defecto es 50]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:703
msgid ""
"Grace period in milliseconds to accept late tunnel build replies after the "
"router has given up waiting. Prevents wasting valid tunnel builds that "
"arrive just after timeout. [Default is 60000 (60 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de gracia en milisegundos para aceptar respuestas de construccion de"
" túnel tardias despues de que el router haya dejado de esperar. Evita "
"desperdiciar construcciones de túnel válidas que llegan justo despues del "
"tiempo de espera. [Por defecto es 60000 (60 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:705
msgid ""
"Minimum target tunnels per pool before triggering urgent rebuild logic. When"
" the number of good tunnels drops below this threshold, the pool escalates "
"to urgent rebuild mode. [Default is 2]"
msgstr ""
"Minimo de túneles objetivo por grupo antes de activar la logica de "
"reconstruccion urgente. Cuando el numero de túneles buenos cae por debajo de"
" este umbral, el grupo escala a modo de reconstruccion urgente. [Por defecto"
" es 2]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:707
msgid ""
"Floor on concurrent next-hop RouterInfo lookups during tunnel build "
"processing. Ensures a minimum level of lookup concurrency even when few "
"tunnels are participating. [Default is 10 (4 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Minimo en busquedas concurrentes de RouterInfo del siguiente salto durante "
"el procesamiento de construccion de túnel. Asegura un nivel minimo de "
"concurrencia de busqueda incluso cuando pocos túneles participan. [Por "
"defecto es 10 (4 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:709
msgid ""
"Ceiling on concurrent next-hop RouterInfo lookups during tunnel build "
"processing. Caps lookup concurrency to prevent overwhelming the netDb. "
"[Default is max(cores/2, 16) (10 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Techo en busquedas concurrentes de RouterInfo del siguiente salto durante el"
" procesamiento de construccion de túnel. Limita la concurrencia de busqueda "
"para evitar abrumar la netDb. [Por defecto es max(nucleos/2, 16) (10 en "
"sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:711
msgid ""
"Percentage of current participating tunnels used to scale the concurrent "
"lookup limit. The effective limit is clamped between minLookupLimit and "
"maxLookupLimit. [Default is 40 (15 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Porcentaje de túneles participantes actuales utilizado para escalar el "
"limite de busquedas concurrentes. El limite efectivo se ajusta entre "
"minLookupLimit y maxLookupLimit. [Por defecto es 40 (15 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:713
msgid ""
"Maximum allowable future skew for tunnel build request timestamps. Requests "
"with timestamps farther in the future than this are rejected as potential "
"replay attacks. [Default is 300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Desviacion futura maxima permitida para marcas de tiempo de solicitudes de "
"construccion de túnel. Las solicitudes con marcas de tiempo mas futuras que "
"esto se rechazan como posibles ataques de repeticion. [Por defecto es 300000"
" (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:715
msgid ""
"Maximum age in milliseconds for tunnel build requests (ElGamal). Requests "
"older than this are rejected as potential replay attacks. Must be >1 hour "
"due to rounding in the protocol. [Default is 3900000 (65 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Edad maxima en milisegundos para solicitudes de construccion de túnel "
"(ElGamal). Las solicitudes mas antiguas que esto se rechazan como posibles "
"ataques de repeticion. Debe ser >1 hora debido al redondeo en el protocolo. "
"[Por defecto es 3900000 (65 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:717
msgid ""
"Maximum age in milliseconds for tunnel build requests (ECIES). ECIES "
"timestamps are rounded to minutes so the tolerance is tighter. [Default is "
"480000 (8 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Edad maxima en milisegundos para solicitudes de construccion de túnel "
"(ECIES). Las marcas de tiempo ECIES se redondean a minutos, por lo que la "
"tolerancia es mas estricta. [Por defecto es 480000 (8 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:719
msgid ""
"Job lag threshold in milliseconds that triggers tunnel build limiting. When "
"router job lag exceeds this value, tunnel build requests are throttled to "
"reduce queue pressure. [Default is 800 (500 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Umbral de retraso de trabajos en milisegundos que activa la limitacion de "
"construccion de túnel. Cuando el retraso de trabajos del router supera este "
"valor, las solicitudes de construccion de túnel se limitan para reducir la "
"presion de la cola. [Por defecto es 800 (500 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:721
msgid ""
"Minimum delay in milliseconds before scheduling a tunnel test. The router "
"will not test a tunnel that was recently tested within this window. [Default"
" is 30000 (30 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Retraso minimo en milisegundos antes de programar una prueba de túnel. El "
"router no probara un túnel que fue probado recientemente dentro de esta "
"ventana. [Por defecto es 30000 (30 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:723
msgid ""
"Maximum delay in milliseconds before scheduling a tunnel test. The router "
"will not defer a tunnel test beyond this limit. [Default is 90000 (90 "
"seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Retraso maximo en milisegundos antes de programar una prueba de túnel. El "
"router no diferira una prueba de túnel mas alla de este limite. [Por defecto"
" es 90000 (90 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:725
msgid ""
"Maximum concurrent tunnel test jobs per exploratory pool. Caps how many "
"exploratory tunnels are tested simultaneously. [Default is 12]"
msgstr ""
"Maximo de trabajos de prueba de túnel concurrentes por grupo exploratorio. "
"Limita cuantos túneles exploratorios se prueban simultáneamente. [Por "
"defecto es 12]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:727
msgid ""
"Maximum concurrent tunnel test jobs per client pool. Caps how many client "
"tunnels are tested simultaneously. [Default is 24]"
msgstr ""
"Maximo de trabajos de prueba de túnel concurrentes por grupo de cliente. "
"Limita cuantos túneles de cliente se prueban simultáneamente. [Por defecto "
"es 24]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:729
msgid ""
"Ratio of tunnels tested vs total pool size that triggers pool coverage "
"heuristics. When fewer than this fraction of tunnels have recent test "
"results, the pool prioritises testing over building. [Default is 0.95]"
msgstr ""
"Proporcion de túneles probados vs tamano total del grupo que activa "
"heuristicas de cobertura del grupo. Cuando menos de esta fraccion de túneles"
" tienen resultados de prueba recientes, el grupo prioriza las pruebas sobre "
"la construccion. [Por defecto es 0.95]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:731
msgid ""
"Cooldown period in milliseconds for client peer selection. Peers selected "
"for a client tunnel are excluded from selection in other client pools for "
"this duration, ensuring peer diversity. [Default is 15000 (15 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de enfriamiento en milisegundos para la seleccion de pares de "
"cliente. Los pares seleccionados para un túnel de cliente son excluidos de "
"la seleccion en otros grupos de cliente durante esta duracion, asegurando "
"diversidad de pares. [Por defecto es 15000 (15 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:733
msgid ""
"Client peer selection strategy: 'default' (balanced, preferred), "
"'reliability' (prioritise proven peers with high tunnel acceptance ratio), "
"or 'diversity' (lower cooldowns, explores broader peer set). Changes apply "
"dynamically. [Default is 'default']"
msgstr ""
"Estrategia de seleccion de pares de cliente: 'default' (equilibrada, "
"preferida), 'reliability' (priorizar pares probados con alta tasa de "
"aceptacion de túneles), o 'diversity' (enfriamientos mas bajos, explora un "
"conjunto de pares mas amplio). Los cambios se aplican dinámicamente. [Por "
"defecto es 'default']"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:735
msgid ""
"Tunnel lifetime in milliseconds. Tunnels expire after this period and are "
"replaced with fresh builds. Lower values increase churn but may improve "
"freshness; higher values reduce build overhead but may accumulate stale "
"tunnels. [Default is 600000 (10 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Vida útil del túnel en milisegundos. Los túneles caducan despues de este "
"periodo y se reemplazan con construcciones nuevas. Valores mas bajos "
"aumentan la rotacion pero pueden mejorar la frescura; valores mas altos "
"reducen la sobrecarga de construccion pero pueden acumular túneles "
"obsoletos. [Por defecto es 600000 (10 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:737
msgid ""
"Startup suppression period in milliseconds. Warnings and tunnel reduction "
"logic are suppressed during initial router startup to avoid premature "
"decisions. [Default is 300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de supresion de inicio en milisegundos. Las advertencias y la logica"
" de reduccion de túneles se suprimen durante el inicio inicial del router "
"para evitar decisiones prematuras. [Por defecto es 300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:739
msgid ""
"Minimum interval in milliseconds between LeaseSet publishes. Prevents rapid "
"publish storms during tunnel churn. [Default is 300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Intervalo minimo en milisegundos entre publicaciones de LeaseSet. Evita "
"tormentas de publicacion durante la rotacion de túneles. [Por defecto es "
"300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:741
msgid ""
"Minimum interval in milliseconds between LeaseSet object builds. Prevents "
"unnecessary LeaseSet object churn on every tunnel add/remove. [Default is "
"300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Intervalo minimo en milisegundos entre construcciones de objetos LeaseSet. "
"Evita la creacion innecesaria de objetos LeaseSet en cada "
"adicion/eliminacion de túnel. [Por defecto es 300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:743
msgid ""
"Maximum number of concurrent tunnel builds per direction. Higher values "
"accelerate pool recovery but may overload the network. [Default is 6]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de construcciones de túnel concurrentes por direccion. Valores"
" mas altos aceleran la recuperacion del grupo pero pueden sobrecargar la "
"red. [Por defecto es 6]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:745
msgid ""
"If exploratory tunnel build success rate falls below 1 in this many "
"attempts, tunnel quantity is reduced. Higher values make quantity reduction "
"less likely. [Default is 12]"
msgstr ""
"Si la tasa de exito de construccion de túnel exploratorio cae por debajo de "
"1 en este numero de intentos, la cantidad de túneles se reduce. Valores mas "
"altos hacen que la reduccion de cantidad sea menos probable. [Por defecto es"
" 12]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:747
msgid ""
"Extra tunnels to maintain beyond the configured pool quantity. A positive "
"value keeps spare tunnels ready so the pool doesn't drain when tunnels "
"expire simultaneously. [Default is 0]"
msgstr ""
"Túneles extra a mantener mas allá de la cantidad configurada del grupo. Un "
"valor positivo mantiene túneles de repuesto listos para que el grupo no se "
"vacie cuando los túneles caducan simultáneamente. [Por defecto es 0]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:749
msgid ""
"Minimum interval in milliseconds between GOOD-tunnel deficit rebuilds for "
"non-critical pools. Prevents rapid build-retry loops when the pool has "
"enough FAILING tunnels to satisfy the numerical target. [Default is 30000 "
"(30 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Intervalo minimo en milisegundos entre reconstrucciones por deficit de "
"túneles GOOD para grupos no críticos. Evita bucles rápidos de reintento de "
"construccion cuando el grupo tiene suficientes túneles FAILING para cumplir "
"el objetivo numérico. [Por defecto es 30000 (30 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:751
msgid ""
"Minimum tunnel test period in milliseconds. Tunnel tests always wait at "
"least this long for a reply before timing out. [Default is 45000 (45 "
"seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo minimo de prueba de túnel en milisegundos. Las pruebas de túnel "
"siempre esperan al menos este tiempo para una respuesta antes de agotar el "
"tiempo de espera. [Por defecto es 45000 (45 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:753
msgid ""
"Maximum tunnel test period in milliseconds. Tunnel tests never wait longer "
"than this for a reply, even on high-latency paths. [Default is 50000 (50 "
"seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo maximo de prueba de túnel en milisegundos. Las pruebas de túnel "
"nunca esperan mas de este tiempo para una respuesta, incluso en rutas de "
"alta latencia. [Por defecto es 50000 (50 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:755
msgid ""
"Number of tunnel build timeouts before a peer is marked as a ghost "
"(blacklisted for tunnel participation). Higher values tolerate more "
"transient failures. [Default is 3]"
msgstr ""
"Numero de tiempos de espera de construccion de túnel antes de que un par sea"
" marcado como fantasma (incluido en lista negra para participacion en "
"túneles). Valores mas altos toleran mas fallos transitorios. [Por defecto es"
" 3]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:757
msgid ""
"Cooldown period in milliseconds before a ghost-marked peer can be considered"
" for tunnel participation again. Shorter values allow faster peer reuse. "
"[Default is 180000 (3 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de enfriamiento en milisegundos antes de que un par marcado como "
"fantasma pueda ser considerado nuevamente para participacion en túneles. "
"Valores mas cortos permiten una reutilizacion mas rapida de pares. [Por "
"defecto es 180000 (3 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:759
msgid ""
"Cooldown period in milliseconds for ghost-marked peers during attack mode. "
"Longer cooldowns limit exposure to potentially malicious peers during high-"
"stress periods. [Default is 300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de enfriamiento en milisegundos para pares marcados como fantasma "
"durante el modo de ataque. Enfriamientos mas largos limitan la exposicion a "
"pares potencialmente maliciosos durante periodos de alto estres. [Por "
"defecto es 300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:761
msgid ""
"Minimum number of incoming tunnel build requests accepted per peer per clean"
" window. Prevents starving peers during low-traffic periods. [Default is 10]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de solicitudes de construccion de túnel entrantes aceptadas "
"por par por ventana limpia. Evita privar a los pares durante periodos de "
"bajo trafico. [Por defecto es 10]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:763
msgid ""
"Maximum number of incoming tunnel build requests accepted per peer per clean"
" window. Caps request volume to prevent DoS. [Default is 300]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de solicitudes de construccion de túnel entrantes aceptadas "
"por par por ventana limpia. Limita el volumen de solicitudes para prevenir "
"DoS. [Por defecto es 300]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:765
msgid ""
"Number of tunnel build requests from a single peer in 1 second that triggers"
" an immediate ban. Protects against rapid-fire DoS attacks. [Default is 10]"
msgstr ""
"Numero de solicitudes de construccion de túnel de un solo par en 1 segundo "
"que activa un baneo inmediato. Protege contra ataques DoS rápidos. [Por "
"defecto es 10]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:767
msgid ""
"Percentage of participating tunnels used to dynamically scale the per-peer "
"request throttle limit. The effective maxLimit is adjusted based on this "
"percentage of current participating tunnel count. [Default is 20]"
msgstr ""
"Porcentaje de túneles participantes utilizado para escalar dinámicamente el "
"limite de regulación por par. El limite maximo efectivo se ajusta basándose "
"en este porcentaje del recuento actual de túneles participantes. [Por "
"defecto es 20]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:769
msgid ""
"Minimum number of participating tunnel build requests accepted per clean "
"window. Ensures a baseline acceptance rate even when the router is under "
"load. [Default is 80 (40 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de solicitudes de construccion de túnel participantes "
"aceptadas por ventana limpia. Asegura una tasa de aceptación basal incluso "
"cuando el router está bajo carga. [Por defecto es 80 (40 en sistemas "
"lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:771
msgid ""
"Maximum number of participating tunnel build requests accepted per clean "
"window. Caps acceptance to prevent overload. [Default is 300 (150 on slow "
"systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de solicitudes de construccion de túnel participantes "
"aceptadas por ventana limpia. Limita la aceptación para evitar sobrecarga. "
"[Por defecto es 300 (150 en sistemas lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:773
msgid ""
"Percentage of current participating tunnels used to scale the participating "
"throttle limits. Higher values allow more build requests relative to tunnel "
"count. [Default is 10]"
msgstr ""
"Porcentaje de túneles participantes actuales utilizado para escalar los "
"limites de regulación participantes. Valores mas altos permiten mas "
"solicitudes de construccion en relacion con el recuento de túneles. [Por "
"defecto es 10]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:775
msgid ""
"Minimum percentage of non-failing peer profiles required before the router "
"broadens exploratory peer selection. When below this threshold, only the "
"most reliable peers are used. [Default is 15]"
msgstr ""
"Porcentaje minimo de perfiles de par no fallidos requerido antes de que el "
"router amplie la seleccion de pares exploratorios. Por debajo de este "
"umbral, solo se utilizan los pares mas confiables. [Por defecto es 15]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:777
msgid ""
"Minimum number of active (non-failing) peers required for normal exploratory"
" peer selection. Below this threshold, selection logic becomes more "
"permissive. [Default is 12]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de pares activos (no fallidos) requerido para la seleccion "
"normal de pares exploratorios. Por debajo de este umbral, la logica de "
"seleccion se vuelve mas permisiva. [Por defecto es 12]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:779
msgid ""
"Minimum number of active peers required during router startup before "
"restricting exploratory peer selection. During early startup the router is "
"more lenient about peer quality. [Default is 6]"
msgstr ""
"Numero minimo de pares activos requerido durante el inicio del router antes "
"de restringir la seleccion de pares exploratorios. Durante el inicio "
"temprano, el router es mas indulgente con la calidad del par. [Por defecto "
"es 6]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:781
msgid ""
"Maximum slow start window size for streaming connections. Caps the "
"congestion window during slow start to prevent overwhelming the network. "
"[Default is 64]"
msgstr ""
"Tamano maximo de ventana de arranque lento para conexiones de flujo. Limita "
"la ventana de congestion durante el arranque lento para evitar abrumar la "
"red. [Por defecto es 64]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:783
msgid ""
"Maximum round-trip time in milliseconds for streaming connections. Caps the "
"computed RTT to prevent pathological timeout values after network "
"disturbances. [Default is 60000 (60 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo maximo de ida y vuelta en milisegundos para conexiones de flujo. "
"Limita el RTT calculado para evitar valores patologicos de tiempo de espera "
"despues de perturbaciones de red. [Por defecto es 60000 (60 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:785
msgid ""
"Maximum number of packet retransmissions before giving up on a connection. "
"Higher values improve reliability on lossy links but delay failure "
"detection. [Default is 64]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de retransmisiones de paquetes antes de abandonar una "
"conexion. Valores mas altos mejoran la confiabilidad en enlaces con perdidas"
" pero retrasan la deteccion de fallos. [Por defecto es 64]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:787
msgid ""
"Cooldown period in milliseconds between connection attempts to the same "
"unreachable destination. Prevents hammering unreachable peers. [Default is "
"60000 (60 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Periodo de enfriamiento en milisegundos entre intentos de conexion al mismo "
"destino inaccesible. Evita golpear repetidamente a pares inaccesibles. [Por "
"defecto es 60000 (60 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:789
msgid ""
"Maximum time in milliseconds to wait for a pong reply when pinging a peer. "
"[Default is 300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo maximo en milisegundos para esperar una respuesta pong al hacer ping "
"a un par. [Por defecto es 300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:791
msgid ""
"Number of times to respond to a throttled destination before silently "
"dropping excess packets. Prevents connection storms from overwhelming the "
"router. [Default is 3]"
msgstr ""
"Numero de veces para responder a un destino limitado antes de descartar "
"silenciosamente paquetes en exceso. Evita que las tormentas de conexion "
"abrumen al router. [Por defecto es 3]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:793
msgid ""
"Default maximum stream delay in milliseconds when no explicit connect "
"timeout is set. [Default is 10000 (10 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Retraso maximo de flujo predeterminado en milisegundos cuando no se "
"establece un tiempo de espera de conexion explícito. [Por defecto es 10000 "
"(10 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:795
msgid ""
"Maximum time in milliseconds between receiving a SYN and accepting it on a "
"server socket. Controls how long incomplete connections are kept in the "
"accept queue. [Default is 4000 (4 seconds)]"
msgstr ""
"Tiempo maximo en milisegundos entre recibir un SYN y aceptarlo en un socket "
"de servidor. Controla cuanto tiempo se mantienen las conexiones incompletas "
"en la cola de aceptacion. [Por defecto es 4000 (4 segundos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:797
msgid ""
"Maximum number of pending connections (SYNs and partial packets) in the "
"server accept queue. Larger values buffer more incoming connections at the "
"cost of memory. [Default is 80 (48 on slow systems)]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de conexiones pendientes (SYNs y paquetes parciales) en la "
"cola de aceptacion del servidor. Valores mas grandes almacenan mas "
"conexiones entrantes a costa de memoria. [Por defecto es 80 (48 en sistemas "
"lentos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:799
msgid ""
"Interval in milliseconds between automated LeaseSet republishes. Higher "
"values reduce netdb traffic but may cause stale lease info. [Default is "
"300000 (5 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Intervalo en milisegundos entre republicaciones automatizadas de LeaseSet. "
"Valores mas altos reducen el trafico de netdb pero pueden causar informacion"
" de concesion obsoleta. [Por defecto es 300000 (5 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:801
msgid ""
"Threshold in milliseconds for proactive LeaseSet republish. If a lease is "
"expiring within this window, the LeaseSet is republished immediately rather "
"than waiting for the next periodic cycle. [Default is 180000 (3 minutes)]"
msgstr ""
"Umbral en milisegundos para republicacion proactiva de LeaseSet. Si una "
"concesion caduca dentro de esta ventana, el LeaseSet se republica "
"inmediatamente en lugar de esperar al siguiente ciclo periodico. [Por "
"defecto es 180000 (3 minutos)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:803
msgid ""
"The period in milliseconds to check for idle tunnels. Tunnels with no "
"traffic for this period may be dropped. [Default is 60000]"
msgstr ""
"El periodo en milisegundos para verificar túneles inactivos. Los túneles sin"
" trafico durante este periodo pueden ser eliminados. [Por defecto es 60000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:805
msgid ""
"The minimum number of messages a tunnel must have processed in the detection"
" period to be considered active. Tunnels below this threshold are candidates"
" for removal. [Default is 3]"
msgstr ""
"El numero minimo de mensajes que un túnel debe haber procesado en el periodo"
" de deteccion para ser considerado activo. Los túneles por debajo de este "
"umbral son candidatos para eliminacion. [Por defecto es 3]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:807
msgid ""
"The interval in milliseconds between scans for idle transit tunnels. "
"[Default is 180000]"
msgstr ""
"El intervalo en milisegundos entre escaneos de túneles de transito "
"inactivos. [Por defecto es 180000]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:809
msgid ""
"If you wish to install unsigned (.zip) I2P updates, this should be added to "
"your <code>router.config</code> file unless you have already configured "
"<code>routerconsole.advanced=true</code>, in which case this option is "
"already provisioned. Note: as of I2P+ 0.9.48+, installation of <a "
"href=/configupdate#i2pupdates>unsigned updates</a> is enabled by default."
msgstr ""
"Si deseas instalar actualizaciones de I2P sin firma (.zip), esto debe "
"agregarse a tu archivo <code>router.config</code> a menos que ya hayas "
"configurado <code>routerconsole.advanced=true</code>, en cuyo caso esta "
"opción ya está habilitada. Nota: a partir de I2P+ 0.9.48+, la instalación de"
" actualizaciones <a href=/configupdate#i2pupdates> sin firma</a> está "
"habilitada de forma predeterminada."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:811
msgid ""
"This setting allows you to configure the update url for the unsigned update "
"feature, if enabled. The url should end with <code>/i2pupdate.zip</code>. "
"Note: do not install unsigned updates unless you trust the source of the "
"update!"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración te permite establecer la URL de actualización para la "
"función de actualización sin firma, si está habilitada. La URL debe terminar"
" con <code>/i2pupdate.zip</code>. ¡Nota: no instales actualizaciones sin "
"firma a menos que confíes en la fuente de la actualización!"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:813
msgid ""
"This setting (in minutes) allows you to manually configure how long to wait "
"after startup before RouterInfos in the NetDb are checked for validity, "
"after which point only valid routers will be accepted for inclusion. When "
"the validation occurs, expired RouterInfos and unresponsive peers only "
"accessible via SSU will be removed from the NetDb. [Default is 60 minutes] "
"Note: This setting has no bearing on older routers (older than 0.9.29 by "
"default) which are removed from the NetDb and banned for the router session "
"as soon as a NetDb store is attempted."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración (en minutos) le permite configurar manualmente cuánto "
"tiempo esperar después del inicio antes de que se verifique la validez de "
"las RouterInfos en NetDb, después de lo cual solo se aceptarán routers "
"válidos para su inclusión. Cuando ocurre la validación, las RouterInfos "
"caducadas y los pares no responden solo accesibles a través de SSU se "
"eliminarán de NetDb. [Predeterminado son 60 minutos] Nota: Esta "
"configuración no tiene relación con los routers más antiguos (más antiguos "
"que la versión 0.9.29 de forma predeterminada), que se eliminarán de NetDb y"
" se prohibirán para la sesión del enrutador en cuanto se intente almacenar "
"NetDb."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:815
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will block direct communication from all "
"routers in your own country and add them to your banlist until your router "
"restarts. [Default is false, or true if router is in hidden mode]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuracion, cuando se activa, bloqueara la comunicacion directa de "
"todos los routers en tu propio pais y los anadira a tu lista de baneos hasta"
" que el router se reinicie. [Por defecto es false, o true si el router esta "
"en modo oculto]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:817
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will block direct communication from all X "
"tier routers that publish a G congestion cap and are neither reachable or "
"unreachable, adding them to the session banlist. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuracion, cuando se activa, bloqueara la comunicacion directa de "
"todos los routers de nivel X que publiquen un limite de congestion G y no "
"sean ni accesibles ni inaccesibles, anadiendolos a la lista de baneos de "
"sesion. [Por defecto es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:819
msgid ""
"This setting, when set to true, will block direct communication from all LU "
"tier routers (low bandwidth, unreachable, or firewalled), adding them to the"
" session banlist. [Default is true]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuracion, cuando se activa, bloqueara la comunicacion directa de "
"todos los routers de nivel LU (bajo ancho de banda, inaccesibles o con "
"cortafuegos), anadiendolos a la lista de baneos de sesion. [Por defecto es "
"true]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:821
msgid ""
"This setting permits disabling SSU tests to determine if your router is "
"firewalled and can be enabled for routers that are definitely not firewalled"
" but are experiencing intermittent firewalling issues. In the event that "
"testing is disabled, both SSU and NTCP should report your current public ip "
"address on <a href=/info>the router info page</a>. [Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite deshabilitar las pruebas de SSU para determinar "
"si tu enrutador está bloqueado por firewall y puede habilitarse para "
"enrutadores que definitivamente no están bloqueados por firewall pero están "
"experimentando problemas intermitentes de firewall. En el caso de que la "
"prueba esté deshabilitada, tanto SSU como NTCP deberían informar tu "
"dirección IP pública actual en <a href=/info>la página de información del "
"enrutador</a>. [Reinicio requerido]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:823
msgid ""
"This setting determines which transport takes priority when communicating "
"with peers. By default, NTCP is favored over UDP (SSU). By setting the value"
" to true, UDP will be favored unless a pre-existing NTCP connection exists; "
"when set to always, UDP will always be used regardless of any pre-existing "
"NTCP connection. [Default is false]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración determina qué transporte tiene prioridad al comunicarse "
"con pares. De forma predeterminada, se favorece NTCP sobre UDP (SSU). Al "
"establecer el valor en true, se favorecerá UDP a menos que exista una "
"conexión NTCP preexistente; cuando se establece en siempre, siempre se usará"
" UDP independientemente de cualquier conexión NTCP preexistente. "
"[Predeterminado es false]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:825
msgid "miscellaneous"
msgstr "varios"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:827
msgid ""
"If set to true, this option will place an icon in the system tray / "
"notification area, with basic service control options. [Disabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Si se establece en true, esta opción colocará un icono en la bandeja del "
"sistema / área de notificación, con opciones básicas de control de "
"servicios. [Deshabilitado de forma predeterminada]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:829
msgid ""
"This setting allows configuration of the maximum number of files per torrent"
" I2PSnark will permit, when downloading or creating a torrent. Note that "
"substantially increasing this value from the default of 2000 files may "
"require additional configuration on the host system to increase the maximum "
"number of open files the operating system will permit (e.g. <code>ulimit "
"-n</code> on Linux). To change, add to I2PSnark's configuration file "
"<code>i2psnark.config</code>. [Restart of I2PSnark or router required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite la configuración del número máximo de archivos "
"por torrent que permitirá Torrentes, al descargar o crear un torrent. Tenga "
"en cuenta que aumentar sustancialmente este valor desde el predeterminado de"
" 2000 archivos puede requerir configuración adicional en el sistema "
"anfitrión para aumentar el número máximo de archivos abiertos que permitirá "
"el sistema operativo (p. ej. <code>ulimit -n</code> en Linux). Para "
"cambiarlo, agréguelo al archivo de configuración de Torrentes "
"<code>i2psnark.config</code>. [Se requiere reiniciar Torrentes o el "
"enrutador]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:831
msgid ""
"This tunnel-specific setting allows you to enable or disable replies to "
"pings sent to servers hosted by the router. To disable pings, you must add "
"the line <code>i2p.streaming.answerPings=false</code> to the <i>Custom "
"Options</i> section for the server's configuration in the Tunnel Manager."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración específica del túnel te permite habilitar o deshabilitar "
"las respuestas a los pings enviados a los servidores alojados por el "
"enrutador. Para deshabilitar los pings, debes agregar la línea "
"<code>i2p.streaming.answerPings=false</code> a la sección <i>Opciones "
"personalizadas</i> de la configuración del servidor en el Administrador de "
"túneles."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:833
msgid ""
"This setting, when enabled, introduces a random pong delay of up to 50ms for"
" all ping-enabled servers hosted by the router. Default is disabled. "
"[Restart required]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando está habilitada, introduce un retardo aleatorio "
"de ping de hasta 50 ms para todos los servidores habilitados para ping "
"alojados por el enrutador. Predeterminado es deshabilitado. [Reinicio "
"requerido]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:835
msgid ""
"This setting, when enabled, modifies the maximum additional random pong "
"delay introduced for ping-enabled servers, if "
"<code>i2p.streaming.enablePongDelay</code> is also enabled. Unless "
"explicitly set, the default value of 50ms will be used."
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración, cuando está habilitada, modifica el retardo aleatorio "
"máximo adicional introducido para los servidores habilitados para ping, si "
"también está habilitado <code>i2p.streaming.enablePongDelay</code>. A menos "
"que se establezca explícitamente, se usará el valor predeterminado de 50ms."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:837
msgid ""
"The connect timeout in milliseconds for eepget HTTP requests (time to wait "
"for initial response headers). Increase for high-latency remote access "
"scenarios. [Default is 90000 (90s)]"
msgstr ""
"El tiempo de espera de conexion en milisegundos para solicitudes HTTP eepget"
" (tiempo para esperar los encabezados de respuesta iniciales). Aumentar para"
" escenarios de acceso remoto de alta latencia. [Por defecto es 90000 (90s)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:839
msgid ""
"The inactivity timeout in milliseconds for eepget transfers (max idle time "
"during data phase). Increase for slow connections experiencing stalls. "
"[Default is 300000 (5min)]"
msgstr ""
"El tiempo de espera de inactividad en milisegundos para transferencias "
"eepget (tiempo maximo inactivo durante la fase de datos). Aumentar para "
"conexiones lentas que experimentan pausas. [Por defecto es 300000 (5min)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:841
msgid ""
"Maximum number of consecutive zero-data transfer failures before eepget "
"gives up, even if retries remain. Increase if transfers fail without "
"receiving any data. [Default is 20]"
msgstr ""
"Numero maximo de fallos consecutivos de transferencia de cero datos antes de"
" que eepget se rinda, incluso si quedan reintentos. Aumentar si las "
"transferencias fallan sin recibir ningún dato. [Por defecto es 20]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:843
msgid ""
"Default number of retries for eepget when the <code>-n</code> flag is not "
"specified. [Default is 10]"
msgstr ""
"Numero predeterminado de reintentos para eepget cuando la bandera "
"<code>-n</code> no se especifica. [Por defecto es 10]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:845
msgid ""
"The TIME-WAIT duration in milliseconds after a streaming connection "
"disconnects, during which late packets are still acknowledged. Increase for "
"high-latency paths where final ACKs may be delayed. [Default is 300000 "
"(5min)]"
msgstr ""
"La duracion TIME-WAIT en milisegundos despues de que una conexion de flujo "
"se desconecta, durante la cual los paquetes tardios aún se reconocen. "
"Aumentar para rutas de alta latencia donde los ACK finales pueden "
"retrasarse. [Por defecto es 300000 (5min)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:847
msgid ""
"The upper bound clamp on streaming connect timeout. Prevents per-connection "
"timeouts from exceeding this ceiling regardless of per-tunnel configuration."
" Increase for very high-latency remote access. [Default is 120000 (2min)]"
msgstr ""
"El limite superior del tiempo de espera de conexion de flujo. Evita que los "
"tiempos de espera por conexion superen este maximo independientemente de la "
"configuracion por túnel. Aumentar para acceso remoto de latencia muy alta. "
"[Por defecto es 120000 (2min)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:849
msgid ""
"Initial congestion window size (in packets) for new streaming connections. A"
" larger window starts connections faster but may cause more retransmissions "
"on congested paths. [Default is 8]"
msgstr ""
"Tamano inicial de la ventana de congestion (en paquetes) para nuevas "
"conexiones de flujo. Una ventana mas grande inicia conexiones mas rapido "
"pero puede causar mas retransmisiones en rutas congestionadas. [Por defecto "
"es 8]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:851
msgid ""
"Maximum congestion window size (in packets) for streaming connections. Caps "
"the maximum throughput of a single stream. [Default is 128]"
msgstr ""
"Tamano maximo de la ventana de congestion (en paquetes) para conexiones de "
"flujo. Limita el rendimiento maximo de un solo flujo. [Por defecto es 128]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:853
msgid ""
"The minimum retransmission delay in milliseconds. Packets will not be resent"
" faster than this interval. Lower values allow faster recovery on lossy "
"connections. [Default is 100ms]"
msgstr ""
"El retraso minimo de retransmision en milisegundos. Los paquetes no se "
"reenviaran mas rapido que este intervalo. Valores mas bajos permiten una "
"recuperacion mas rapida en conexiones con perdidas. [Por defecto es 100ms]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:855
msgid ""
"The maximum retransmission delay in milliseconds. Retransmit interval will "
"not exceed this value regardless of backoff. Increase to allow longer "
"between retries on congested paths. [Default is 30000 (30s)]"
msgstr ""
"El retraso maximo de retransmision en milisegundos. El intervalo de "
"retransmision no superara este valor independientemente del retroceso. "
"Aumentar para permitir mas tiempo entre reintentos en rutas congestionadas. "
"[Por defecto es 30000 (30s)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:857
msgid ""
"The maximum Retransmission TimeOut in milliseconds after exponential backoff"
" (doubling). Caps how long the sender waits before attempting retransmission"
" during severe congestion. [Default is 30000 (30s)]"
msgstr ""
"El tiempo maximo de espera de retransmision en milisegundos despues del "
"retroceso exponencial (duplicacion). Limita cuanto tiempo espera el emisor "
"antes de intentar la retransmision durante congestion severa. [Por defecto "
"es 30000 (30s)]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:859
msgid ""
"When set to true, I2P runs without network connectivity, which is helpful if"
" you are constantly restarting the router to test code updates as this "
"prevents network disruption."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se establece en true, I2P se ejecuta sin conectividad de red, lo que "
"es útil si estás reiniciando constantemente el enrutador para probar "
"actualizaciones de código, ya que esto evita la interrupción de la red."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:861
msgid ""
"When set to true, disables local-local loopback delivery and forces all "
"traffic through tunnels (outbound tunnel → network → inbound tunnel → local "
"destination). Useful for testing tunnel routing behavior when the source and"
" destination are on the same router. [Disabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se activa, deshabilita la entrega de bucle local-local y fuerza todo "
"el trafico a través de túneles (túnel de salida → red → túnel de entrada → "
"destino local). Útil para probar el comportamiento de enrutamiento de "
"túneles cuando el origen y el destino están en el mismo router. "
"[Deshabilitado por defecto]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/advancedsettings_jsp.java:863
msgid ""
"This setting permits the configuration of alternative NTP servers required "
"to ensure that your router maintains accurate clock time. [Default is "
"0.pool.ntp.org,1.pool.ntp.org,2.pool.ntp.org]"
msgstr ""
"Esta configuración permite la configuración de servidores NTP alternativos "
"requeridos para garantizar que su enrutador mantenga la hora correcta. "
"[Predeterminado es 0.pool.ntp.org,1.pool.ntp.org,2.pool.ntp.org]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/changelog_jsp.java:473
msgid "Recent I2P+ Changes"
msgstr "Cambios recientes en I2P+"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/changelog_jsp.java:488
msgid "View the full change log"
msgstr "Ver el registro de cambios completo"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:467
#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/ui_jsp.java:578
msgid ""
"While I2P will work fine behind most firewalls, your speeds and network "
"integration will generally improve if the I2P port is forwarded for both UDP"
" and TCP."
msgstr ""
"Aunque I2P funcionará detrás de la mayoría de cortafuegos, las velocidades e"
" integración en la red generalmente mejorarán si el puerto de I2P es "
"retransmitido tanto por UDP como por TCP."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:471
msgid ""
"If you can, please poke a hole in your firewall to allow unsolicited UDP and"
" TCP packets to reach you."
msgstr ""
"Si es posible, por favor permita el paso por el cortafuegos hasta usted de "
"los paquetes TCP y UDP no solicitados."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:473
msgid ""
"If you can't, I2P supports UPnP (Universal Plug and Play) and UDP hole "
"punching with \"SSU introductions\" to relay traffic."
msgstr ""
"Si no puede, para repetir el tráfico I2P soporta UPnP (Universal Plug and "
"Play) y apertura dinámica (hole punching) de UDP mediante \"introducciones "
"SSU\"."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:475
msgid ""
"Most of the options on the Network Configuration page are for special "
"situations, for example where UPnP does not work correctly, or a firewall "
"not under your control is doing harm."
msgstr ""
"La mayoría de las opciones en la página 'Configuración de red' son para "
"situaciones especiales, por ejemplo, donde UPnP no funciona correctamente o "
"un cortafuegos fuera de su control está causando daño."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:477
msgid "Certain firewalls such as symmetric NATs may not work well with I2P."
msgstr ""
"Puede que algunos cortafuegos, como aquellos con NATs simétricos, no "
"funcionen bien con I2P."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:479
msgid ""
"UPnP is used to communicate with Internet Gateway Devices (IGDs) to detect "
"the external IP address and forward ports."
msgstr ""
"UPnP se utiliza para comunicarse con dispositivos de pasarela a Internet "
"(IGDs), para detectar la dirección IP externa y retransmitir hacia esta los "
"puertos."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:481
msgid "UPnP support is beta, and may not work for any number of reasons"
msgstr ""
"El soporte de UPnP está en fase beta, y puede no funcionar por varias "
"razones"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:483
msgid "No UPnP-compatible device present"
msgstr "No se encontró ningún dispositivo con compatibilidad UPnP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:485
msgid "UPnP disabled on the device"
msgstr "UPnP deshabilitado en el dispositivo"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:487
msgid "Software firewall interference with UPnP"
msgstr "Un software cortafuegos interfiere con UPnP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:489
msgid "Bugs in the device's UPnP implementation"
msgstr "Fallos en la implementación UPnP del dispositivo"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:491
msgid "Multiple firewall/routers in the internet connection path"
msgstr "Múltiples cortafuegos/routers en la ruta de conexión a Internet"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:493
msgid "UPnP device change, reset, or address change"
msgstr ""
"El dispositivo UPnP fue reemplazado, reiniciado, o ha cambiado de dirección"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:495
msgid ""
"UPnP may be enabled or disabled on the Network Configuration page, but a "
"change requires a router restart to take effect."
msgstr ""
"UPnP puede estar habilitado o deshabilitado en la página de Configuración de"
" Red, pero si se cambia se requiere un reinicio del router para que se "
"aplique."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:497
msgid "Review the UPnP status here."
msgstr "Revise el estado de UPnP aquí."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:499
msgid ""
"Also, <b>do not enter a private IP address</b> like 127.0.0.1 or "
"192.168.1.1."
msgstr ""
"Además, <b>no debe introducir una dirección IP privada</b> como 127.0.0.1 o "
"192.168.1.1."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:501
msgid ""
"If you specify the wrong IP address, or do not properly configure your NAT "
"or firewall, your network performance will degrade substantially."
msgstr ""
"Si especifica una dirección IP incorrecta o no configura correctamente su "
"NAT o cortafuegos, su rendimiento de red se degradará sustancialmente."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:503
msgid "When in doubt, leave the settings at the defaults."
msgstr "En caso de duda, deje los ajustes con los valores predeterminados."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:505
msgid "Web Browser Configuration"
msgstr "Configuración del navegador web"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:507
msgid ""
"In order to access websites hosted on I2P, and optionally use the default "
"outproxy to connect to websites on clearnet, you will need to configure your"
" browser to use the I2P HTTP proxy, by default running on <code>127.0.0.1 "
"port 4444</code>. Most browsers offer an option to configure your proxy; in "
"this mini-tutorial we'll focus on Firefox."
msgstr ""
"Para acceder a sitios web alojados en I2P y, opcionalmente, usar el proxy de"
" salida predeterminado para conectarse a sitios web en clearnet, deberá "
"configurar su navegador para usar el proxy HTTP de I2P, que se ejecuta de "
"forma predeterminada en <code>127.0.0.1 puerto 4444</code>. La mayoría de "
"los navegadores ofrecen una opción para configurar su proxy; en este mini "
"tutorial nos centraremos en Firefox."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:509
msgid ""
"Open the Preferences page in Firefox and scroll to the bottom of the General"
" section."
msgstr ""
"Abra la página de Preferencias en Firefox y desplácese hasta la parte "
"inferior de la sección General."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:511
msgid "In the Network Settings sub-section, hit the <i>Settings</i> button."
msgstr ""
"En la subsección de Configuración de red, haga clic en el botón "
"<i>Ajustes</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:513
msgid ""
"Under <i>Configure Proxy Access to Internet</i> select the <i>Manual proxy "
"configuration</i> option."
msgstr ""
"Debajo de <i>Configurar acceso de proxy a Internet</i>, seleccione la opción"
" <i>Configuración manual del proxy</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:515
msgid ""
"Enter <code>127.0.0.1</code> in the <i>HTTP Proxy</i> field, and "
"<code>4444</code> in the <i>Port</i> field."
msgstr ""
"Introduzca <code>127.0.0.1</code> en el campo <i>Proxy HTTP</i> y "
"<code>4444</code> en el campo <i>Puerto</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:517
msgid ""
"Tick the box marked <i>Use this proxy server for all protocols</i> to avoid "
"requests escaping the proxy."
msgstr ""
"Marque la casilla <i>Usar este servidor proxy para todos los protocolos</i> "
"para evitar que las solicitudes escapen del proxy."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:519
msgid ""
"In the box marked <i>No Proxy for</i> add the line "
"<code>127.0.0.1,localhost</code> to ensure the I2P console and other locally"
" hosted websites are still available."
msgstr ""
"En el cuadro marcado como <i>Sin proxy para</i>, agregue la línea "
"<code>127.0.0.1, localhost</code> para asegurar que la consola I2P y otros "
"sitios web alojados localmente sigan disponibles."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:521
msgid ""
"Tick the box marked <i>Proxy DNS when using SOCKS v5</i> to prevent DNS "
"leaks."
msgstr ""
"Marque la casilla <i>Proxy DNS al usar SOCKS v5</i> para evitar fugas de "
"DNS."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:523
msgid ""
"Hit the <i>OK</i> button and test the proxy is working by visiting <a "
"href=http://planeta.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>planeta.i2p</a> and <a href=https://www.myip.com/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>www.myip.com</a>."
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en el botón <i>Aceptar</i> y pruebe que el proxy funciona "
"visitando <a href=http://planeta.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>planeta.i2p</a> y <a href=https://www.myip.com/ target=_blank"
" rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>www.myip.com</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:525
msgid ""
"Note: To enhance your security when browsing .i2p sites, you may wish to "
"consider installing an addon to prevent Javascript from running in the "
"browser such as <a href=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-"
"US/firefox/addon/noscript/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink "
"external'>NoScript</a>, though it's recommended to whitelist the address "
"I2P+ is running on to enable various router console enhancements. In "
"addition, an addon that prevents requests to offsite resources is also "
"recommended, for example <a href=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-"
"US/firefox/addon/umatrix/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink "
"external'>uMatrix</a>."
msgstr ""
"Nota: Para mejorar su seguridad al navegar sitios .i2p, puede considerar "
"instalar un addon para evitar que Javascript se ejecute en el navegador, "
"como <a href=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/noscript/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>NoScript</a>, aunque "
"se recomienda permitir la dirección en la que se ejecuta I2P+ para habilitar"
" diversas mejoras de la consola del enrutador. Además, se recomienda un "
"addon que impida las solicitudes a recursos externos, como <a "
"href=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/umatrix/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>uMatrix</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:527
msgid ""
"For a more extensive guide to configuration for various browsers, see the <a"
" href=https://geti2p.net/en/about/browser-config target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>browser configuration guide</a>."
msgstr ""
"Para una guía más extensa sobre la configuración de varios navegadores, "
"consulte la <a href=https://geti2p.net/es/about/browser-config target=_blank"
" rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>guía de configuración de "
"navegadores</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:529
msgid "The Tunnel Manager"
msgstr "El administrador de túneles"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:531
msgid ""
"The Tunnel Manager enables configuration of local services provided by your "
"router."
msgstr ""
"El Administrador de túneles permite configurar los servicios locales "
"proporcionados por su enrutador."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:533
msgid ""
"You can determine which services automatically start when the router starts,"
" manage tunnel allocation to optimize for high usage services or to minimize"
" the the cpu and memory overhead, add server and client tunnels to host or "
"access services on the network, set rate limiting or tunnel filtering for "
"your server tunnels and more."
msgstr ""
"Puede determinar qué servicios se inician automáticamente al iniciar el "
"enrutador, administrar la asignación de túneles para optimizarlos en función"
" de los servicios de alto uso o minimizar la sobrecarga de CPU y memoria, "
"agregar túneles de servidor y cliente para alojar o acceder a servicios en "
"la red, establecer limitaciones de velocidad o filtrado de túneles para sus "
"túneles de servidor y más."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:535
msgid ""
"By default, most of your client services (mail, http proxy, IRC) will share "
"the same set of tunnels (for performance reasons) and be listed as <i>Shared"
" Clients</i> and <i>Shared Clients(DSA)</i> in the sidebar under Service "
"Tunnels and on the <a href=/tunnels>Tunnels page</a>."
msgstr ""
"De forma predeterminada, la mayoría de sus servicios cliente (correo, proxy "
"HTTP, IRC) compartirán el mismo conjunto de túneles (por razones de "
"rendimiento) y se enumerarán como <i>Clientes compartidos</i> y <i>Clientes "
"compartidos (DSA)</i> en la barra lateral bajo Túneles de servicio y en la "
"página <a href=/tunnels>Túneles</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:537
msgid ""
"However, if you experience a tunnel failure, all your services will go "
"offline at the same time, so in some scenarios you may wish to configure "
"client services to use their own set of tunnels."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, si experimenta una falla de túnel, todos sus servicios se "
"desconectarán al mismo tiempo, por lo que en algunos escenarios es posible "
"que desee configurar los servicios cliente para que usen su propio conjunto "
"de túneles."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:539
msgid ""
"This can be done by unchecking the <i>Share tunnels with other configured "
"clients</i> option listed under <i>Shared Client</i> on the configuration "
"page of the relevant client service, after which you will need to restart "
"the client service from the <a href=/i2ptunnelmgr>Tunnel Manager index "
"page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Esto se puede hacer desmarcando la opción <i>Compartir túneles con otros "
"clientes configurados</i> que se enumera debajo de <i>Cliente compartido</i>"
" en la página de configuración del servicio cliente correspondiente, después"
" de lo cual deberá reiniciar el servicio cliente desde la <a "
"href=/i2ptunnelmgr>página de índice del administrador de túneles</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/configuration_jsp.java:541
msgid ""
"Note: Most of the options in the Tunnel Manager have tooltips; be sure to "
"check those before you change settings you don't fully understand!"
msgstr ""
"¡Nota: La mayoría de las opciones en el administrador de túneles tienen "
"información sobre herramientas; ¡asegúrese de revisarlas antes de cambiar "
"configuraciones que no comprenda completamente!"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:470
msgid "Abridged I2P FAQ"
msgstr "Preguntas frecuentes de I2P abreviado"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:472
msgid ""
"This is a shortened version of the official FAQ. For the full version, "
"please visit <a href=https://geti2p.net/faq target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class='sitelink external'>https://geti2p.net/faq</a> or <a "
"href=http://i2p-projekt.i2p/faq target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://i2p-projekt.i2p/faq</a>."
msgstr ""
"Esta es una versión abreviada de las Preguntas Frecuentes oficiales. Para la"
" versión completa, visite <a href=https://geti2p.net/faq target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>https://geti2p.net/faq</a> o <a "
"href=http://i2p-projekt.i2p/faq target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://i2p-projekt.i2p/faq</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:474
msgid ""
"My router has been up for several minutes and has zero or very few "
"connections"
msgstr ""
"Mi enrutador ha estado en funcionamiento durante varios minutos y tiene cero"
" o muy pocas conexiones"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:476
msgid ""
"If after a few minutes of uptime your router is indicating 0 Active Peers "
"and 0 Known Peers, with a notification in the sidebar that you need to check"
" your network connection, verify that you can access the internet. If your "
"internet connection is functional, you may need to unblock Java in your "
"firewall. Otherwise, you may need to reseed your I2P router. Visit the <a "
"href=/configreseed#reseedconfig>Reseed Configuration page</a> and click the "
"<i>Save Changes and Reseed Now</i> button. For more information, see the <a "
"href=#reseedhelp>Reseed help section</a> above."
msgstr ""
"Si después de unos minutos de funcionamiento su enrutador indica 0 peers "
"activos y 0 peers conocidos, con una notificación en la barra lateral de que"
" debe verificar su conexión de red, compruebe que puede acceder a Internet. "
"Si su conexión a Internet funciona, es posible que necesite desbloquear Java"
" en su cortafuegos. De lo contrario, es posible que deba volver a sembrar su"
" enrutador I2P. Visite la página <a href=/configreseed#reseedconfig>Reseed "
"Configuration</a> y haga clic en el botón <i>Guardar cambios y volver a "
"sembrar ahora</i>. Para más información, consulte la sección <a "
"href=#reseedhelp>Ayuda para volver a sembrar</a> anterior."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:478
msgid "My router has very few active peers, is this OK?"
msgstr "Mi enrutador tiene muy pocos peers activos, ¿esto está bien?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:480
msgid ""
"If your router has 10 or more active peers, everything is fine. The router "
"should maintain connections to a few peers at all times. The best way to "
"stay \"better-connected\" to the network is to <a href=/config>share more "
"bandwidth</a>."
msgstr ""
"Si su enrutador tiene 10 o más peers activos, todo está bien. El enrutador "
"debe mantener conexiones con unos pocos peers en todo momento. La mejor "
"manera de permanecer \"mejor conectado\" a la red es <a "
"href=/config>compartir más ancho de banda</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:482
msgid ""
"I'm missing lots of hosts in my addressbook. What are some good subscription"
" links?"
msgstr ""
"Me faltan muchos anfitriones en mi libreta de direcciones. ¿Cuáles son "
"algunos buenos enlaces de suscripción?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:484
msgid ""
"The default subscription is to <code>http://i2p-projekt.i2p/hosts.txt</code>"
" which is seldom updated. If you don't have another subscription, you may "
"often have to use \"jump\" links which is much slower but ensures that your "
"addressbook is only populated by sites you use (in addition to the default "
"subscription addresses). To speed up browsing on I2P, it's a good idea to "
"add some addressbook subscriptions."
msgstr ""
"La suscripción predeterminada es a "
"<code>http://i2p-projekt.i2p/hosts.txt</code>, que rara vez se actualiza. Si"
" no tiene otra suscripción, a menudo tendrá que usar enlaces de \"salto\" "
"que es mucho más lento pero garantiza que su libreta de direcciones solo se "
"puebla con sitios que usa (además de las direcciones de suscripción "
"predeterminadas). Para acelerar la navegación en I2P, es una buena idea "
"agregar algunas suscripciones a la libreta de direcciones."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:486
msgid ""
"Here are some other public addressbook subscription links. You may wish to "
"add one or two to your <a href='/dns?subscriptions' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>susidns subscription list</a>. In the event that addresses "
"conflict in the subscriptions, the lists placed at the top of your susidns "
"configuration will take precedence over those placed further down."
msgstr ""
"Aquí hay algunos otros enlaces de suscripción a la libreta de direcciones "
"pública. Puede que desees añadir uno o dos a tu <a href='/dns?subscriptions'"
" target=_blank rel=noreferrer>lista de suscripciones de susidns</a>. En caso"
" de que haya conflictos de direcciones en las suscripciones, las listas "
"colocadas en la parte superior de tu configuración de susidns tendrán "
"precedencia sobre las que se encuentren más abajo."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:488
msgid ""
"Note that subscribing to a hosts.txt service is an act of trust, as a "
"malicious subscription could give you incorrect addresses, so be careful "
"subscribing to lists from unknown sources. The operators of these services "
"may have various policies for listing hosts. Presence on this list does not "
"imply endorsement."
msgstr ""
"Ten en cuenta que suscribirte a un servicio hosts.txt es un acto de "
"confianza, ya que una suscripción maliciosa podría darte direcciones "
"incorrectas, así que ten cuidado al suscribirte a listas de fuentes "
"desconocidas. Los operadores de estos servicios pueden tener varias "
"políticas para listar hosts. La presencia en esta lista no implica un "
"respaldo."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:490
msgid ""
"How do I access IRC, BitTorrent, or other services on the regular Internet?"
msgstr "¿Cómo accedo a IRC, BitTorrent u otros servicios en Internet regular?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:492
msgid ""
"Unless an outproxy has been set up for the service you want to connect to, "
"this is not possible, with the exception of BitTorrent (see below). There "
"are only three types of outproxies running right now: HTTP, HTTPS, and "
"email. Note that there is currently no publicly listed SOCKS outproxy. If "
"this type of service is required, try <a href=https://torproject.org/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Tor</a>."
msgstr ""
"A menos que se haya configurado un outproxy para el servicio al que quieras "
"conectarte, esto no es posible, con la excepción de BitTorrent (ver más "
"abajo). Actualmente sólo hay tres tipos de outproxies en funcionamiento: "
"HTTP, HTTPS y correo electrónico. Ten en cuenta que actualmente no hay "
"ningún outproxy SOCKS listado públicamente. Si se requiere este tipo de "
"servicio, prueba <a href=https://torproject.org/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Tor</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:494
msgid "Can I download torrents from non-I2P trackers?"
msgstr "¿Puedo descargar torrents de rastreadores no I2P?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:496
msgid ""
"Until the advent of I2P integration in <a href=http://www.vuze.com/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Vuze</a>, it wasn't "
"possible to download torrents that weren't hosted on the I2P network. "
"However, now that Vuze (and latterly <a href=https://www.biglybt.com/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Bigly</a>) allow "
"users to share non-I2P torrents on I2P, non-I2P torrents can be downloaded "
"over I2P if Vuze/Bigly users have chosen to make content available to the "
"I2P network. Popular torrents with a large number of peers are more likely "
"to be accessible via I2P; to determine if the content is available, add the "
"torrent link, magnet or infohash to your I2P-enabled BitTorrent client."
msgstr ""
"Hasta la aparición de la integración de I2P en <a href=http://www.vuze.com/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Vuze</a>, no era "
"posible descargar torrents que no estuvieran alojados en la red I2P. Sin "
"embargo, ahora que Vuze (y posteriormente <a href=https://www.biglybt.com/ "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Bigly</a>) permiten a"
" los usuarios compartir torrents no I2P en I2P, los torrents no I2P se "
"pueden descargar a través de I2P si los usuarios de Vuze/Bigly han decidido "
"poner el contenido a disposición de la red I2P. Los torrents populares con "
"un gran número de pares son más susceptibles de ser accesibles a través de "
"I2P; para determinar si el contenido está disponible, añade el enlace del "
"torrent, magnet o infohash a tu cliente de BitTorrent habilitado para I2P."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:498
msgid "How do I configure I2P to open at startup in a specific web browser?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo configuro I2P para que se abra al inicio en un navegador web "
"específico?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:500
msgid ""
"By default, I2P will use the system configured default browser to launch at "
"startup. If you wish to nominate an alternative browser, you will need to "
"edit your router.config file (or the <a href=/configadvanced>Advanced "
"Configuration page</a> if you have enabled advanced console mode) and add a "
"new configuration line <code>routerconsole.browser=/path/to/browser</code> "
"or <code>routerconsole.browser=\\path\\to\\browser.exe</code> if using "
"Windows, replacing <code>\\path\\to\\browser</code> with the location of the"
" browser you wish to use. Note: If the path to your chosen browser contains "
"spaces, you may need to encase the path in quotes e.g. "
"<code>routerconsole.browser=\"C:\\Program "
"Files\\Mozilla\\Firefox.exe\"</code>"
msgstr ""
"Por defecto, I2P usará el navegador predeterminado del sistema para "
"iniciarse. Si deseas seleccionar un navegador alternativo, deberás editar el"
" archivo router.config (o la <a href=/configadvanced>página de configuración"
" avanzada</a> si has habilitado el modo de consola avanzado) y añadir una "
"nueva línea de configuración "
"<code>routerconsole.browser=/ruta/al/navegador</code> o "
"<code>routerconsole.browser=\\ruta\\al\\navegador.exe</code> si usas "
"Windows, reemplazando <code>\\ruta\\al\\navegador</code> con la ubicación "
"del navegador que deseas usar. Nota: Si la ruta a tu navegador elegido "
"contiene espacios, puede que necesites encapsular la ruta entre comillas, "
"p.ej. <code>routerconsole.browser=\"C:\\Archivos de "
"programa\\Mozilla\\Firefox.exe\"</code>"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:502
msgid "How do I configure my browser to access .i2p websites?"
msgstr "¿Cómo configuro mi navegador para acceder a sitios web .i2p?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:504
msgid ""
"You will need to configure your browser to use the HTTP proxy server (by "
"default on host: <code>127.0.0.1</code> port: <code>4444</code>). See the <a"
" href=https://geti2p.net/en/about/browser-config target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Browser Proxy Configuration "
"Guide</a> for a more detailed explanation."
msgstr ""
"Deberás configurar tu navegador para usar el servidor proxy HTTP (por "
"defecto en host: <code>127.0.0.1</code> puerto: <code>4444</code>). Consulta"
" la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/about/browser-config target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>Guía de configuración del proxy del"
" navegador</a> para una explicación más detallada."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:506
msgid "What is an eepsite?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un eepsite?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:508
msgid ""
"An eepsite is a website that is hosted anonymously on the I2P network - you "
"can access it by configuring your web browser to use I2P's HTTP proxy (see "
"above) and browsing to the <code>.i2p</code> suffixed website (e.g. <a "
"href=http://i2p-projekt.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://i2p-projekt.i2p</a>). Also ensure your browser is "
"configured to resolve DNS remotely when using the proxy to avoid DNS leaks."
msgstr ""
"Un eepsite es un sitio web alojado de forma anónima en la red I2P - puedes "
"acceder a él configurando tu navegador web para usar el proxy HTTP de I2P "
"(ve arriba) y navegando al sitio web con el sufijo <code>.i2p</code> (p. ej."
" <a href=http://i2p-projekt.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://i2p-projekt.i2p</a>). Asegúrate también de que tu "
"navegador esté configurado para resolver DNS de forma remota al usar el "
"proxy para evitar fugas de DNS."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:510
msgid "Most of the eepsites are down?"
msgstr "¿La mayoría de los eepsites están caídos?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:512
msgid ""
"If you consider every eepsite that has ever been created, yes, most of them "
"are down. People and eepsites come and go. A good way to get started in I2P "
"is check out a list of eepsites that are currently up. <a "
"href=http://notbob.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://notbob.i2p</a> tracks active eepsites."
msgstr ""
"Si consideras todos los eepsites que se han creado, sí, la mayoría están "
"caídos. La gente y los eepsites van y vienen. Una buena manera de empezar en"
" I2P es revisar una lista de eepsites que actualmente estén funcionando. <a "
"href=http://notbob.i2p/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>http://notbob.i2p</a> lleva un seguimiento de los eepsites "
"activos."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:514
msgid "Where are my I2P configuration files stored?"
msgstr "¿Dónde se almacenan los archivos de configuración de I2P?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:516
msgid ""
"Configuration files for the router, installed plugins, and router logs are "
"stored in the following location:"
msgstr ""
"Los archivos de configuración del enrutador, plugins instalados y registros "
"del enrutador se almacenan en la siguiente ubicación:"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:518
msgid "Windows"
msgstr "ventanas"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:520
msgid "OS X"
msgstr "OS X / MacOS"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:522
msgid "Linux"
msgstr "linux"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:524
msgid "Standard Java Installation"
msgstr "Instalación estándar de Java"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:526
msgid "Package / repository installation"
msgstr "Instalación de paquete / repositorio"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:528
msgid "How do I enable https:// access for the router console?"
msgstr "¿Cómo habilito el acceso https:// para la consola del enrutador?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:530
msgid ""
"Locate the configuration file: "
"<code>00-net.i2p.router.web.RouterConsoleRunner-clients.config</code> in the"
" <code>clients.config.d</code> folder in your I2P settings directory, and "
"then edit accordingly:"
msgstr ""
"Ubica el archivo de configuración: "
"<code>00-net.i2p.router.web.RouterConsoleRunner-clients.config</code> en la "
"carpeta <code>clients.config.d</code> en tu directorio de configuraciones de"
" I2P, y edita de la siguiente manera:"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:532
msgid "For both non-SSL and SSL"
msgstr "Para no SSL y SSL"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:534
msgid "For SSL only"
msgstr "Sólo para SSL"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:536
msgid ""
"How can I configure the console and web services to be accessible on my "
"local network?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puedo configurar la consola y los servicios web para que sean "
"accesibles en mi red local?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:538
msgid ""
"To make your console accessible on your local network, edit the "
"configuration file 00-net.i2p.router.web.RouterConsoleRunner-clients.config "
"in the clients.config.d folder of your I2P settings directory. Update or add"
" the necessary IP addresses to the existing localhost (127.0.0.1) mapping. "
"Use the -s switch for HTTPS access."
msgstr ""
"Para hacer que su consola sea accesible en su red local, edite el archivo de"
" configuración 00-net.i2p.router.web.RouterConsoleRunner-clients.config en "
"la carpeta clients.config.d de su directorio de configuración I2P. Actualice"
" o agregue las direcciones IP necesarias al mapeo localhost existente "
"(127.0.0.1). Use el interruptor -s para acceso HTTPS."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:540
msgid ""
"Example: To allow access from both localhost and 192.168.1.10 over HTTP and "
"HTTPS:"
msgstr ""
"Ejemplo: Para permitir acceso desde localhost y 192.168.1.10 sobre HTTP y "
"HTTPS:"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:542
msgid ""
"For most client services, change the listening address for the relevant "
"service in the Tunnel Manager's configuration section using the <i>reachable"
" by</i> dropdown."
msgstr ""
"Para la mayoría de servicios de cliente, cambie la dirección de escucha para"
" el servicio relevante en la sección de configuración del Gestor de túneles "
"usando el menú desplegable <i>alcance por</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:544
msgid "How do I connect to IRC within I2P?"
msgstr "¿Cómo me conecto a IRC dentro de I2P?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:546
msgid ""
"A tunnel to the main IRC server network within I2P, Irc2P, is created when "
"I2P is installed (see the <a href=/i2ptunnelmgr>Tunnel Manager</a>), and is "
"automatically started when the I2P router starts. To connect to it, tell "
"your IRC client to connect to server: <code>127.0.0.1</code> port: "
"<code>6668</code>."
msgstr ""
"Cuando se instala I2P se crea un túnel hacia la red principal de servidores "
"IRC dentro de I2P, Irc2P, (vea el <a href=/i2ptunnelmgr>Gestor de "
"túneles</a>), y se inicia automáticamente cuando arranca el enrutador I2P. "
"Para conectarte, indícale a tu cliente IRC que se conecte al servidor: "
"<code>127.0.0.1</code> puerto: <code>6668</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:548
msgid ""
"XChat-like client users can create a new network with the server "
"<code>127.0.0.1/6668</code> (remember to tick <i>Bypass proxy server</i> if "
"you have a proxy server configured), or you can connect with the command "
"<code>/server 127.0.0.1 6668</code>. Different IRC clients may vary the "
"syntax."
msgstr ""
"Los usuarios de clientes similares a XChat pueden crear una nueva red con el"
" servidor <code>127.0.0.1/6668</code> (recuerda seleccionar <i>Bypass proxy "
"server</i> si tienes un servidor proxy configurado), o puedes conectarte con"
" el comando <code>/server 127.0.0.1 6668</code>. La sintaxis puede variar "
"según el cliente IRC."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:550
msgid ""
"My IRC client keeps disconnecting from the network, is there anything I can "
"do?"
msgstr ""
"¿Mi cliente IRC se desconecta continuamente de la red, hay algo que pueda "
"hacer?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:552
msgid ""
"Some IRC clients are configured to disconnect from the server if there's "
"been no communication with the server for a period of time, which can "
"sometimes be problematic for I2P IRC if the <i>ping timeout</i> value is set"
" too low. Setting the ping timeout value in your client to a high value "
"(e.g. 320 seconds) will often result in a more robust connection to the "
"network. In hexchat you can configure the value by typing <code>/set "
"net_ping_timeout 320</code>. This will write the value to your "
"<code>hexchat.conf</code> file."
msgstr ""
"Algunos clientes IRC están configurados para desconectarse del servidor si "
"no hay comunicación con él durante un periodo de tiempo, lo que en ocasiones"
" puede ser un problema para IRC de I2P si el valor de <i>tiempo de espera de"
" ping</i> está establecido demasiado bajo. Establecer el valor de tiempo de "
"espera de ping en tu cliente en un valor alto (p.ej. 320 segundos) "
"generalmente dará como resultado una conexión más robusta a la red. En "
"HexChat puedes configurar el valor escribiendo <code>/set net_ping_timeout "
"320</code>. Esto escribirá el valor en tu archivo <code>hexchat.conf</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:554
msgid "What ports does I2P use?"
msgstr "¿Qué puertos usa I2P?"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:556
msgid "LOCAL PORTS"
msgstr "PUERTOS LOCALES"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:558
msgid ""
"These are the local I2P port mappings, listening only to local connections "
"by default, except where noted. Unless you require access from other "
"machines, they should only be accessible from localhost."
msgstr ""
"Estos son los mapeos de puertos locales de I2P, escuchando solo conexiones "
"locales por defecto, excepto donde se indique. A menos que requieras acceso "
"desde otras máquinas, solo deberían ser accesibles desde localhost."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:562
msgid "Function"
msgstr "Función"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:564
msgid "Notes"
msgstr "Notas"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:566
msgid "UPnP SSDP UDP multicast listener"
msgstr "Escuchador UDP multicast SSDP UPnP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:568
msgid ""
"Cannot be changed. Binds to all interfaces. Can be disabled on the <a "
"href=/confignet>Network Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"No puede ser cambiado. Se une a todas las interfaces. Puede desactivarse en "
"la página de <a href=/confignet>Configuración de red</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:570
msgid "BOB bridge"
msgstr "Puente BOB"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:572
msgid ""
"A higher level socket API for clients. Can be enabled/disabled on the <a "
"href=/configclients>Client Configuration page</a>. Can be changed in the "
"<code>bob.config</code> file. [Disabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Una API de sockets de nivel superior para clientes. Puede "
"habilitarse/deshabilitarse en la página de <a "
"href=/configclients>Configuración de clientes</a>. Puede modificarse en el "
"archivo <code>bob.config</code>. [Deshabilitado por defecto]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:574
msgid "HTTP proxy"
msgstr "Proxy HTTP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:576
#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:580
#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:584
#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:616
#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:620
msgid ""
"Can be disabled or changed in the <a href=/i2ptunnelmgr>Tunnel Manager</a>. "
"Can also be configured to bind to a specific interface or all interfaces."
msgstr ""
"Puede deshabilitarse o cambiarse en el <a href=/i2ptunnelmgr>Gestor de "
"túneles</a>. También puede configurarse para unirse a una interfaz "
"específica o a todas las interfaces."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:578
msgid "HTTPS proxy"
msgstr "Proxy HTTPS"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:582
msgid "IRC proxy"
msgstr "Proxy IRC"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:586
msgid "UPnP HTTP TCP event listener"
msgstr "Escuchador de eventos HTTP TCP UPnP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:588
msgid ""
"Binds to the LAN address. Can be changed with advanced config "
"<code>i2np.upnp.HTTPPort=nnnn</code>. Can be disabled on the <a "
"href=/confignet>Network Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Se une a la dirección LAN. Puede cambiarse con configuración avanzada "
"<code>i2np.upnp.HTTPPort=nnnn</code>. Puede deshabilitarse en la página de "
"<a href=/confignet>Configuración de red</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:590
msgid "UPnP SSDP UDP search response listener"
msgstr "Escuchador de respuestas de búsqueda UDP SSDP UPnP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:592
msgid ""
"Binds to all interfaces. Can be changed with advanced config "
"<code>i2np.upnp.SSDPPort=nnnn</code>. Can be disabled on the <a "
"href=/configclients>Client Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Se une a todas las interfaces. Puede cambiarse con configuración avanzada "
"<code>i2np.upnp.SSDPPort=nnnn</code>. Puede deshabilitarse en la página de "
"<a href=/configclients>Configuración de clientes</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:594
msgid "I2P Client Protocol port"
msgstr "Puerto del protocolo de cliente I2P"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:596
msgid ""
"Used by client apps. Can be changed to a different port on the <a "
"href=/configclients>Client Configuration page</a> but this is not "
"recommended. Can be bound to a different interface or all interfaces, or "
"disabled, on the <a href=/configclients>Client Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Utilizado por aplicaciones cliente. Puede cambiarse a un puerto diferente en"
" la página <a href=/configclients>Configuración de clientes</a> pero no se "
"recomienda. Puede unirse a una interfaz diferente o a todas las interfaces, "
"o deshabilitarse, en la página <a href=/configclients>Configuración de "
"clientes</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:598
msgid "UDP for SAM bridge"
msgstr "UDP para el puente SAM"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:600
msgid ""
"A higher level socket API for clients. Only opened when a SAM V3 client "
"requests a UDP session. Can be enabled/disabled on the <a "
"href=/configclients> Client Configuration page</a>. Can be changed in the "
"<code>clients.config</code> file with the SAM command line option "
"<code>sam.udp.port=nnnn</code>."
msgstr ""
"Una API de sockets de nivel superior para clientes. Solo se abre cuando un "
"cliente SAM V3 solicita una sesión UDP. Puede habilitarse/deshabilitarse en "
"la página <a href=/configclients>Configuración de clientes</a>. Puede "
"cambiarse en el archivo <code>clients.config</code> con la opción de línea "
"de comandos SAM <code>sam.udp.port=nnnn</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:602
msgid "SAM bridge"
msgstr "Puente SAM"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:604
msgid ""
"A higher level socket API for clients. Can be enabled/disabled on the <a "
"href=/configclients>Client Configuration page</a>. Can be changed in the "
"<code>clients.config</code> file. [Disabled by default]"
msgstr ""
"Una API de sockets de nivel superior para clientes. Puede "
"habilitarse/deshabilitarse en la página <a href=/configclients>Configuración"
" de clientes</a>. Puede cambiarse en el archivo <code>clients.config</code>."
" [Deshabilitado por defecto]"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:606
msgid "I2P Router Console (Web interface)"
msgstr "Consola del enrutador I2P (interfaz web)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:608
msgid ""
"Can be disabled in the <code>clients.config</code> file. Can also be "
"configured to bind to a specific interface or all interfaces. If you make "
"the Router Console available over the network, you might wish to <a "
"href=/configui#passwordheading>enforce an access password</a> to prevent "
"unauthorized access."
msgstr ""
"Puede deshabilitarse en el archivo <code>clients.config</code>. También "
"puede configurarse para unirse a una interfaz específica o a todas las "
"interfaces. Si haces disponible la Consola del Enrutador a través de la red,"
" es posible que desees <a href=/configui#passwordheading>imponer una "
"contraseña de acceso</a> para evitar accesos no autorizados."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:612
msgid ""
"Can be disabled in the <code>clients.config</code> file. Can also be "
"configured to bind to a specific interface or all interfaces in the "
"<code>jetty.xml</code> file."
msgstr ""
"Puede deshabilitarse en el archivo <code>clients.config</code>. También "
"puede configurarse para unirse a una interfaz específica o a todas las "
"interfaces en el archivo <code>jetty.xml</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:614
msgid "Outgoing mail to smtp.postman.i2p"
msgstr "Correo saliente a smtp.postman.i2p"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:618
msgid "Incoming mail from pop.postman.i2p"
msgstr "Correo entrante de pop.postman.i2p"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:622
msgid "I2P Router Console (https://)"
msgstr "Consola del enrutador I2P (https://)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:624
msgid ""
"Can be enabled in the <code>clients.config</code> file. Can also be "
"configured to bind to a specific interface or all interfaces. If both http "
"and https are enabled, automatic redirection to https is enabled by default."
" If you make the Router Console available over the network, you might wish "
"to <a href=/configui#passwordheading>enforce an access password</a> to "
"prevent unauthorized access."
msgstr ""
"Puede habilitarse en el archivo <code>clients.config</code>. También puede "
"configurarse para unirse a una interfaz específica o a todas las interfaces."
" Si se habilitan http y https, la redirección automática a https está "
"habilitada de forma predeterminada. Si haces disponible la Consola del "
"Enrutador a través de la red, es posible que desees <a "
"href=/configui#passwordheading>imponer una contraseña de acceso</a> para "
"evitar accesos no autorizados."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:626
msgid "Local connection to wrapper control channel port"
msgstr "Conexión local al puerto de canal de control del envoltorio"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:628
msgid ""
"Outbound to 32000 only, does not listen on this port. Starts at 31000 and "
"will increment until 31999 looking for a free port. To change, see the <a "
"href=https://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/prop-port.html "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>wrapper "
"documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Solo saliente a 32000, no escucha en este puerto. Comienza en 31000 e "
"incrementa hasta 31999 buscando un puerto libre. Para cambiar, ve la <a "
"href=https://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/prop-port.html "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>documentación del "
"envoltorio</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:630
msgid "Local control channel for the service wrapper"
msgstr "Canal de control local para el envoltorio de servicio"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:632
msgid ""
"To change, see the <a "
"href=https://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/prop-port.html "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>wrapper "
"documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Para cambiar, ve la <a "
"href=https://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/prop-port.html "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer class='sitelink external'>documentación del "
"envoltorio</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:634
msgid "INTERNET FACING PORTS"
msgstr "PUERTOS HACIA INTERNET"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:636
msgid ""
"I2P selects a random port between 9000 and 31000 to communicate with other "
"routers when the program is run for the first time, or when your external IP"
" address changes when running in <a href=/confignet#ipchange>Laptop "
"Mode</a>. The <a href=/confignet#udpconfig>selected port</a> is shown on the"
" <a href=/confignet>Network Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"I2P selecciona un puerto aleatorio entre 9000 y 31000 para comunicarse con "
"otros enrutadores cuando el programa se ejecuta por primera vez, o cuando "
"cambia tu dirección IP externa al ejecutarse en <a "
"href=/confignet#ipchange>modo portátil</a>. El puerto <a "
"href=/confignet#udpconfig>seleccionado</a> se muestra en la <a "
"href=/confignet>página de configuración de red</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:638
msgid ""
"Outbound UDP from the <a href=/confignet#udpconfig>random port</a> noted on "
"the Network Configuration page to arbitrary remote UDP ports, allowing "
"replies."
msgstr ""
"UDP saliente desde el puerto <a href=/confignet#udpconfig>aleatorio</a> "
"indicado en la página de configuración de red hacia puertos UDP remotos "
"arbitrarios, permitiendo respuestas."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:640
msgid "Outbound TCP from random high ports to arbitrary remote TCP ports."
msgstr ""
"TCP saliente desde puertos altos aleatorios hacia puertos TCP remotos "
"arbitrarios."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:642
msgid ""
"Inbound UDP to the <a href=/confignet#udpconfig>port</a> noted on the "
"Network Configuration page from arbitrary locations (optional, but "
"recommended)."
msgstr ""
"UDP entrante hacia el puerto <a href=/confignet#udpconfig>indicado</a> en la"
" página de configuración de red desde ubicaciones arbitrarias (opcional, "
"pero recomendado)."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:644
msgid ""
"Inbound TCP to the <a href=/confignet#externaltcp>port</a> noted on the "
"Network Configuration page from arbitrary locations (optional, but "
"recommended). <a href=/confignet#tcpconfig>Inbound TCP</a> may be disabled "
"on the Network Configuration page."
msgstr ""
"TCP entrante hacia el puerto <a href=/confignet#externaltcp>indicado</a> en "
"la página de configuración de red desde ubicaciones arbitrarias (opcional, "
"pero recomendado). El <a href=/confignet#tcpconfig>TCP entrante</a> se puede"
" deshabilitar en la página de configuración de red."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/faq_jsp.java:646
msgid ""
"Outbound UDP on port 123, allowing replies: this is necessary for I2P's "
"internal time sync (via SNTP - querying a random SNTP host in "
"<code>pool.ntp.org</code> or <a "
"href=/help/advancedsettings#ntpserverconfig>another server you specify</a>)."
msgstr ""
"UDP saliente en el puerto 123, permitiendo respuestas: esto es necesario "
"para la sincronización de tiempo interna de I2P (a través de SNTP - "
"consultando un host SNTP aleatorio en <code>pool.ntp.org</code> o <a "
"href=/help/advancedsettings#ntpserverconfig>otro servidor que "
"especifiques</a>)."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:470
msgid "I2P Terminology"
msgstr "Terminología de I2P"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:474
msgid ""
"An I2P web application that manages service destinations for the network, "
"mapping B64 hashes to human-readable names. Destinations may be added "
"manually, or via subscriptions to hosts.txt files. Also referred to as "
"SusiDNS. For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/naming class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Una aplicación web de I2P que gestiona destinos de servicio para la red, "
"mapeando hashes B64 a nombres legibles por humanos. Los destinos se pueden "
"añadir manualmente o a través de subscripciones a archivos hosts.txt. "
"También se conoce como DNS. Para más información, consultar la <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/naming class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:476
msgid "Base32 (B32) / Base64 (B64)"
msgstr "Base32 (B32) / Base64 (B64)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:478
msgid ""
"A <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base32 class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base32</a> link (which always ends with "
".b32.i2p) is a hash of a <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64 "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base64</a> "
"destination. For services on the network, the Base64 hash is often mapped to"
" an .i2p domain in the addressbook."
msgstr ""
"Un enlace <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base32 class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base32</a> (que siempre termina en "
".b32.i2p) es un hash de un destino <a "
"href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64 class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base64</a>. Para los servicios de la red, el "
"hash Base64 a menudo se mapea a un dominio .i2p en la libreta de "
"direcciones."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:480
msgid "B33"
msgstr "B33"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:482
msgid ""
"An address containing an encrypted LeaseSet is informally referred to as a "
"b33 address, an extension of a base32 address with the host's public key and"
" signature type encoded into the address instead of a lookup hash. This "
"address type is required for blinded Leasesets. More information: <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/spec/b32encrypted class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>B33 Specification</a>"
msgstr ""
"A una dirección que contiene un LeaseSet cifrado se le suele llamar "
"dirección b33, una extensión de una dirección base32 con la clave pública "
"del host y el tipo de firma codificados en la dirección en lugar de un hash "
"de búsqueda. Este tipo de dirección se requiere para los Leasesets "
"enmascarados. Más información: <a href=https://geti2p.net/spec/b32encrypted "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Especificación "
"B33</a>"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:484
msgid "BOB"
msgstr "CHELÍN"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:486
msgid ""
"BOB (Basic Open Bridge) is a (now-deprecated) simple application-to-router "
"protocol, superseded by <i>SAM</i>. For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/api/bob class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"BOB (Basic Open Bridge) es un protocolo sencillo de aplicación-a-rutador "
"(ahora en desuso), sustituido por <i>SAM</i>. Para más información, consulta"
" la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/api/bob class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:488
msgid "Clearnet"
msgstr "red clara"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:490
msgid ""
"Clearnet normally refers to the publicly accessible internet, the opposite "
"of the darknet that typically describes the encrypted, anonymous services "
"built on I2P, Tor etc. For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clearnet_(networking) class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Wikipedia article</a>."
msgstr ""
"Clearnet normalmente se refiere a Internet accesible públicamente, lo "
"opuesto a la darknet que típicamente describe los servicios encriptados y "
"anónimos construidos sobre I2P, Tor, etc. Para más información, consulta el "
"<a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clearnet_(networking) class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>artículo de Wikipedia</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:494
msgid ""
"The unique cryptographic identity of the inbound endpoint of a tunnel "
"providing access to a service on the I2P network, represented as a Base32 or"
" Base64 hash of the public key. Equivalent to an IP address and port."
msgstr ""
"La identidad criptográfica única del punto final entrante de un túnel que "
"proporciona acceso a un servicio en la red I2P, representada como un hash "
"Base32 o Base64 de la clave pública. Equivalente a una dirección IP y "
"puerto."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:496
msgid "Eepget"
msgstr "Eepget"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:498
msgid ""
"A command-line application supplied with I2P that is used to request URL "
"resources, similar to <a href=https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/ "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>wget</a> or <a "
"href=https://curl.haxx.se/ class='sitelink external' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>curl</a>. Eepget is also used internally by the router, for "
"example to reseed from remote hosts. By default, eepget uses the HTTP proxy "
"on <code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."
msgstr ""
"Una aplicación de línea de comandos suministrada con I2P que se usa para "
"solicitar recursos de URL, similar a <a "
"href=https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/ class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>wget</a> o <a href=https://curl.haxx.se/ "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>curl</a>. Eepget "
"también se usa internamente por el enrutador, por ejemplo para volver a "
"sembrar desde hosts remotos. Por defecto, eepget usa el proxy HTTP en "
"<code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:500
msgid "Eephead"
msgstr "cabeza de ep"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:502
msgid ""
"A command-line application supplied with I2P+ (Linux/MacOS) that is used to "
"perform a <code>head</code> request on a specified http resource on the "
"network, returning various response headers from the remote server. By "
"default, eephead uses the HTTP proxy on <code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."
msgstr ""
"Una aplicación de línea de comandos suministrada con I2P+ (Linux/MacOS) que "
"se usa para realizar una solicitud <code>head</code> sobre un recurso http "
"especificado en la red, devolviendo varios encabezados de respuesta del "
"servidor remoto. Por defecto, eephead usa el proxy HTTP en "
"<code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:504
msgid "Eepsite"
msgstr "Sitio web"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:506
msgid ""
"A website hosted on the I2P network. By default, a <a "
"href=https://www.eclipse.org/jetty/about.html class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Jetty webserver</a> is configured and running "
"on <a href=http://127.0.0.1:7658/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>http://127.0.0.1:7658/</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un sitio web alojado en la red I2P. Por defecto, un <a "
"href=https://www.eclipse.org/jetty/about.html class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>servidor web Jetty</a> está configurado y "
"ejecutándose en <a href=http://127.0.0.1:7658/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>http://127.0.0.1:7658/</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:508
msgid "Exploratory Tunnel"
msgstr "Túnel exploratorio"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:510
msgid ""
"A tunnel used by the router for communicating with other routers to perform "
"various \"housekeeping\" functions such as learning and publishing "
"<i>leasesets</i>, testing client tunnels, and learning about and validating "
"other routers in the network. These tunnels are normally low-bandwidth."
msgstr ""
"Un túnel utilizado por el enrutador para comunicarse con otros enrutadores "
"para realizar diversas funciones de \"mantenimiento\" como aprender y "
"publicar <i>leasesets</i>, probar túneles de cliente y aprender y validar "
"otros enrutadores en la red. Estos túneles normalmente tienen una baja ancho"
" de banda."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:514
msgid ""
"A router on the network tasked with providing and receiving information "
"about other routers and services on the network. The current minimum share "
"bandwidth for a router to be considered as capable of performing floodfill "
"duties is 128 KBytes/sec, though it's possible to override this requirement "
"and force a router to be a floodfill on the <a href=/configadvanced>Advanced"
" Configuration page</a>. For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/network-database#floodfill "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online "
"documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un enrutador en la red responsable de proporcionar e intercambiar "
"información sobre otros enrutadores y servicios en la red. El ancho de banda"
" compartido mínimo actual para que un enrutador se considere capaz de "
"realizar las funciones de floodfill es de 128 KBytes/seg, aunque es posible "
"anular este requisito y forzar a un enrutador a ser un floodfill en la <a "
"href=/configadvanced>página de configuración avanzada</a>. Para más "
"información, consulta la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/network-"
"database#floodfill class='sitelink external' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:516
msgid "Garlic Routing"
msgstr "Enrutamiento con Ajos"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:518
msgid ""
"A variant of onion routing that encrypts multiple messages together to make "
"it more difficult for attackers to perform traffic analysis and to increase "
"the speed of data transfer. For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/garlic-routing class='sitelink external'"
" target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Una variante del enrutamiento cebolla que cifra varios mensajes juntos para "
"dificultar el análisis de tráfico por atacantes y aumentar la velocidad de "
"transferencia de datos. Para más información, consulta la <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/garlic-routing class='sitelink external'"
" target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:520
msgid "Hidden Mode"
msgstr "Modo Oculto"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:522
msgid ""
"A router configured to run in Hidden Mode will not publish its details to "
"the <i>Network Database</i> and will not participate in routing traffic for "
"other routers. Routers operating in countries designated as strict and "
"routers manually configured run in Hidden Mode."
msgstr ""
"Un enrutador configurado para ejecutarse en Modo Oculto no publicará sus "
"detalles en la <i>Base de Datos de Red</i> y no participará en el "
"enrutamiento de tráfico para otros enrutadores. Los enrutadores que operan "
"en países designados como estrictos y los enrutadores configurados "
"manualmente funcionan en Modo Oculto."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:526
msgid ""
"The I2P Client Protocol (I2CP) enables external applications (clients) to "
"communicate with I2P over single TCP socket, by default using port 7654. For"
" more information, see the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/protocol/i2cp "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online "
"documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"El Protocolo Cliente I2P (I2CP) permite que aplicaciones externas (clientes)"
" se comuniquen con I2P a través de un único socket TCP, usando por defecto "
"el puerto 7654. Para más información, consulta la <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/protocol/i2cp class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:528
msgid "I2NP"
msgstr "I2NP"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:530
msgid ""
"The I2P Network Protocol (I2NP) manages the routing and mixing of messages "
"between routers, in addition to the transport selection (where more than one"
" is supported) when communicating with a peer. For more information, see the"
" <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/protocol/i2np class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"El Protocolo de Red I2P (I2NP) gestiona el enrutamiento y mezcla de mensajes"
" entre enrutadores, además de la selección del transporte (cuando se apoya "
"más de uno) al comunicarse con un par. Para más información, consulta la <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/protocol/i2np class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:532
msgid "I2P+"
msgstr "I2P+"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:534
msgid ""
"A soft fork of the Java I2P software which retains full compatibility, "
"providing an enhanced user interface and improvements to network "
"performance. See <a href=http://skank.i2p/ class=sitelink target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>http://skank.i2p/</a> or <a href=https://i2pplus.github.io "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>https://i2pplus.github.io</a>for more information."
msgstr ""
"Una bifurcación blanda del software Java I2P que mantiene la compatibilidad "
"total, proporcionando una interfaz de usuario mejorada y mejoras en el "
"rendimiento de red. Ver <a href=http://skank.i2p/ class=sitelink "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>http://skank.i2p/</a> o <a "
"href=https://i2pplus.github.io class='sitelink external' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>https://i2pplus.github.io</a>para más información."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:536
msgid "I2PBote (plugin)"
msgstr "I2PBote (complemento)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:538
msgid ""
"An unmaintained I2P plugin that provides serverless, end-to-end encrypted "
"e-mail within the I2P network. For more information, see <a "
"href=http://bote.i2p/ class=sitelink target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>http://bote.i2p/</a>. Source code is available on <a "
"href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.i2p-bote class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un complemento I2P sin mantener que provee correo electrónico cifrado de "
"extremo a extremo y sin servidor dentro de la red I2P. Para más información,"
" ver <a href=http://bote.i2p/ class=sitelink target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>http://bote.i2p/</a>. El código fuente está disponible en <a "
"href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.i2p-bote class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:540
msgid "i2pd"
msgstr "i2pd"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:542
msgid ""
"An alternative implementation of an I2P router coded in C++. For more "
"information, see <a href=https://i2pd.website/ class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>https://i2pd.website/</a> Source code is "
"available on <a href=https://github.com/PurpleI2P/i2pd class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."
msgstr ""
"Una implementación alternativa de un enrutador I2P codificado en C++. Para "
"más información, ver <a href=https://i2pd.website/ class='sitelink external'"
" target=_blank rel=noreferrer>https://i2pd.website/</a> El código fuente "
"está disponible en <a href=https://github.com/PurpleI2P/i2pd class='sitelink"
" external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:546
msgid ""
"A fork of the <a href=http://www.klomp.org/snark/ class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Snark BitTorrent client</a> refactored for use "
"on the I2P network. Usually supplied as part of the default suite of "
"applications with Java I2P, and also available as a <a "
"href=http://skank.i2p/#download class=sitelink target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>standalone Java application</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un fork del cliente BitTorrent <a href=http://www.klomp.org/snark/ "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Snark</a> "
"refactorizado para su uso en la red I2P. Generalmente incluido como parte "
"del conjunto de aplicaciones predeterminadas de Java I2P, y también "
"disponible como una <a href=http://skank.i2p/#download class=sitelink "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>aplicación Java independiente</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:548
msgid "Introducer"
msgstr "Introductor"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:550
msgid ""
"A router that facilitates the connection to the network of another router "
"that is behind a firewall."
msgstr ""
"Un enrutador que facilita la conexión a la red de otro enrutador que se "
"encuentra detrás de un firewall."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:552
msgid "Jump Service"
msgstr "Servicio Saltarín"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:554
msgid ""
"A simple CGI application that takes a hostname as a parameter and returns a "
"301 redirect to the proper URL with a <code>?i2paddresshelper=key</code> "
"string appended. The HTTP proxy will interpret the appended string and use "
"the key as the actual destination. In addition, the proxy will cache the key"
" so the address helper is not necessary until restart, and offer the option "
"to add the resolved address to the addressbook."
msgstr ""
"Una aplicación CGI sencilla que toma un nombre de host como parámetro y "
"retorna una redirección 301 a la URL correcta con la cadena "
"<code>?i2paddresshelper=key</code> agregada. El proxy HTTP interpretará la "
"cadena agregada y usará la clave como el destino real. Además, el proxy "
"almacenará la clave en caché de modo que no sea necesario el auxiliar de "
"direcciones hasta el reinicio, y ofrecerá la opción de agregar la dirección "
"resuelta a la libreta de direcciones."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:556
msgid "Laptop Mode"
msgstr "Modo Portátil"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:558
msgid ""
"An <a href=/confignet#ipchange>optional configuration</a> that automatically"
" changes your <a href=/netdb?r=.>router identity</a> and <a "
"href=/confignet#udpconfig>external port</a> when the public ip address your "
"system is on changes. This can prevent an adversary from correlating your "
"router identity and ip address in scenarios where your ip address may change"
" frequently, for example when you're running I2P on a laptop from multiple "
"locations."
msgstr ""
"Una <a href=/confignet#ipchange>configuración opcional</a> que cambia "
"automáticamente tu <a href=/netdb?r=.>identidad de router</a> y el <a "
"href=/confignet#udpconfig>puerto externo</a> cuando cambia la dirección IP "
"pública de tu sistema. Esto puede evitar que un adversario correlacione tu "
"identidad de router y dirección IP en escenarios donde tu dirección IP pueda"
" cambiar frecuentemente, por ejemplo cuando ejecutas I2P en una laptop desde"
" múltiples ubicaciones."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:560
msgid "Lease"
msgstr "Alquiler"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:562
msgid ""
"The information that defines the authorization for a particular tunnel to "
"receive messages targeting a <i>Destination</i>."
msgstr ""
"La información que define la autorización para que un túnel en particular "
"reciba mensajes dirigidos a un <i>Destino</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:566
msgid ""
"A group of tunnel entry points (leases) for a <i>destination</i>. Note: A "
"0-hop server tunnel will only have one lease, regardless of the number of "
"tunnels configured."
msgstr ""
"Un grupo de puntos de entrada de túnel (arriendos) para un <i>destino</i>. "
"Nota: Un túnel servidor de 0 saltos solo tendrá un arriendo, "
"independientemente del número de túneles configurados."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:568
msgid "Monotone / mtn"
msgstr "Monótono / mtn"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:570
msgid ""
"The distributed version control system (DVCS) previously used to maintain "
"I2P's source code, now superseded by git."
msgstr ""
"El sistema de control de versiones distribuido (DVCS) previamente usado para"
" mantener el código fuente de I2P, ahora reemplazado por git."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:572
msgid "Multihoming"
msgstr "multihoming"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:574
msgid ""
"Services may be hosted on multiple routers simultaneously, by sharing the "
"same private key for the destination. Multihoming can further enhance the "
"security and stability of a server by providing redundancy; if a server is "
"multihomed, when a server in the pool goes offline, the provided service "
"will remain available, making it more difficult to correlate server downtime"
" with a router going offline."
msgstr ""
"Los servicios se pueden alojar en múltiples enrutadores simultáneamente, "
"compartiendo la misma clave privada para el destino. Multihoming puede "
"mejorar aún más la seguridad y estabilidad de un servidor al proporcionar "
"redundancia; si un servidor está multihoming, cuando un servidor en el grupo"
" se desconecta, el servicio provisto permanecerá disponible, dificultando la"
" correlación de tiempo fuera de línea de un servidor con un enrutador que se"
" desconecta."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:578
msgid ""
"A distributed database containing router contact information (RouterInfos) "
"and destination contact information (LeaseSets). A single router maintains "
"its own (partial) database for communicating with other routers on the "
"network; no single router will maintain a list of all routers. The "
"RouterInfos are stored on disk and read into memory when the router starts, "
"or when new RouterInfos are acquired. Also referred to as the <i>NetDb</i>. "
"For more information, see the <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/network-database class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"Una base de datos distribuida que contiene información de contacto de "
"enrutadores (RouterInfos) e información de contacto de destinos (LeaseSets)."
" Un solo enrutador mantiene su propia base de datos (parcial) para "
"comunicarse con otros enrutadores en la red; ningún enrutador mantendrá una "
"lista de todos los enrutadores. Los RouterInfos se almacenan en disco y se "
"leen en memoria cuando el enrutador se inicia o cuando se adquieren nuevos "
"RouterInfos. También se le refiere como <i>NetDb</i>. Para más información, "
"consulta la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/how/network-database "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en "
"línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:580
msgid "NTCP / NTCP2"
msgstr "NTCP/NTCP2"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:582
msgid ""
"NTCP (NIO-based TCP) and NTCP2 are TCP-based network transports which use "
"Java's NIO (New I/O) TCP implementation to deliver I2NP messages between "
"routers on the network. NTCP2 improves the resistance of NTCP to various "
"attacks and automated traffic identification methods. For more information, "
"see the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/transport/ntcp class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"NTCP (TCP basado en NIO) y NTCP2 son transportes de red basados en TCP que "
"usan la implementación TCP de Java NIO (Entrada/Salida Nueva) para entregar "
"mensajes I2NP entre enrutadores en la red. NTCP2 mejora la resistencia de "
"NTCP a diversos ataques y métodos de identificación automática de tráfico. "
"Para más información, consulta la <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/transport/ntcp class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:584
msgid "Orchid (plugin)"
msgstr "Orchid (complemento)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:586
msgid ""
"A java implementation of a Tor client, available as an I2P plugin. Can be "
"used as the default <i>outproxy</i> if configured in the relevant SOCKS or "
"HTTP client tunnel in the <i>Tunnel Manager</i>. Available from <a "
"href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins "
"class=sitelink>http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins</a>. Source code is available on"
" <a href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.plugins.orchid class='sitelink external'"
" target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."
msgstr ""
"Una implementación en Java de un cliente Tor, disponible como un complemento"
" de I2P. Puede usarse como <i>outproxy</i> predeterminado si se configura en"
" el túnel SOCKS o HTTP cliente correspondiente en el <i>Administrador de "
"Túneles</i>. Disponible desde <a href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins "
"class=sitelink>http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins</a>. El código fuente está "
"disponible en <a href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.plugins.orchid "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:588
msgid "Outproxy"
msgstr "Superar proxy"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:590
msgid ""
"A service on the network that provides a proxy connection to the "
"<i>clearnet</i>. By default, I2P has an HTTP outproxy configured for web "
"browsing on <code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."
msgstr ""
"Un servicio en la red que proporciona una conexión proxy a la "
"<i>clearnet</i>. Por defecto, I2P tiene configurado un outproxy HTTP para "
"navegar por la web en <code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:592
msgid "Participation"
msgstr "Participación"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:594
msgid ""
"The act of contributing to the network by permitting other routers to build "
"tunnels using your router in a tunnel chain. At least 12KB/s upstream "
"bandwidth (network share) is required to be allocated in order to enable "
"participation. Note that firewalled routers will be limited in how much they"
" contribute to participation, and a router designated as Hidden will not "
"participate at all."
msgstr ""
"El acto de contribuir a la red permitiendo que otros enrutadores construyan "
"túneles usando tu enrutador en una cadena de túneles. Se requiere asignar al"
" menos 12KB/s de ancho de banda de subida (compartir red) para habilitar la "
"participación. Ten en cuenta que los enrutadores con firewall estarán "
"limitados en cuanto a su contribución a la participación, y un enrutador "
"designado como Oculto no participará en absoluto."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:598
msgid ""
"The process of acquiring router identities, normally via <i>clearnet</i> "
"servers, to ensure your router can communicate and build tunnels with other "
"routers on the network. When a router has no router identities for other "
"peers (usually immediately after installation), the process of reseeding is "
"also referred to as <i>bootstrapping</i>."
msgstr ""
"El proceso de adquirir identidades de enrutador, normalmente a través de "
"servidores de <i>clearnet</i>, para garantizar que tu enrutador pueda "
"comunicarse y construir túneles con otros enrutadores en la red. Cuando un "
"enrutador no posee identidades de otros pares (generalmente inmediatamente "
"después de la instalación), al proceso de volver a sembrar también se le "
"refiere como <i>inicio</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:602
msgid ""
"The core I2P software, which routes encrypted packets on the I2P network. "
"All routers by default participate in the network except routers running in "
"countries considered hostile (see <i>Strict Countries</i>), which both helps"
" the network and provides cover traffic for any clients or servers "
"connecting to the I2P network through the router."
msgstr ""
"El software central de I2P, que enruta paquetes cifrados en la red I2P. Por "
"defecto, todos los enrutadores participan en la red excepto los enrutadores "
"que funcionan en países considerados hostiles (ver <i>Países Estrictos</i>),"
" lo cual ayuda tanto a la red como al tráfico de cobertura para cualquier "
"cliente o servidor que se conecte a la red I2P a través del enrutador."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:604
msgid "Router Identity"
msgstr "Identidad de Enrutador"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:606
msgid ""
"Information defining the unique identity of a router on the network which "
"includes its IP address (or the IP addresses of intermediate introducers) "
"and listening port, public signing and encryption keys. Router identities "
"correlate to peers in the NetDB. Also referred to as a <i>RouterInfo</i>."
msgstr ""
"Información que define la identidad única de un enrutador en la red, la cual"
" incluye su dirección IP (o las direcciones IP de introductores intermedios)"
" y puerto de escucha, claves públicas de firma y cifrado. Las identidades de"
" enrutador se correlacionan con pares en NetDB. También se le refiere como "
"<i>RouterInfo</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:610
msgid ""
"SAM (Simple Anonymous Messaging) is a protocol which allows a client "
"application written in any programming language to communicate over I2P, by "
"using a socket-based interface to the I2P router. For more information, see "
"the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/api/samv3 class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"SAM (Mensajería Anónima Simple) es un protocolo que permite a una aplicación"
" cliente escrita en cualquier lenguaje de programación comunicarse a través "
"de I2P, utilizando una interfaz basada en sockets con el enrutador I2P. Para"
" más información, consulta la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/api/samv3 "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en "
"línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:612
msgid "Shared Client"
msgstr "Cliente Compartido"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:614
msgid ""
"In order to use a single set of tunnels for multiple client services, "
"clients can be configured from the <i>Tunnel Manager</i> to operate in "
"<i>Shared Client</i> mode. This mode conserves resources and blends the "
"traffic from multiple clients into a single set of tunnels, making traffic "
"analysis harder. Clients configured as Shared Clients share the same tunnel "
"options."
msgstr ""
"Para usar un único conjunto de túneles para múltiples servicios cliente, los"
" clientes se pueden configurar desde el <i>Administrador de Túneles</i> para"
" operar en modo <i>Cliente Compartido</i>. Este modo conserva recursos y "
"mezcla el tráfico de múltiples clientes en un único conjunto de túneles, "
"dificultando el análisis de tráfico. Los clientes configurados como Clientes"
" Compartidos comparten las mismas opciones de túneles."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:618
msgid ""
"SSU (Secure Semi-reliable UDP) is an I2P network transport providing "
"encrypted, connection-oriented, point-to-point connections, in addition to "
"IP address detection and NAT traversal services. For more information, see "
"the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/transport/ssu class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
msgstr ""
"SSU (UDP Semiseguro Seguro) es un transporte de red I2P que proporciona "
"conexiones punto a punto cifradas y orientadas a conexión, además de "
"servicios de detección de direcciones IP y traversal de NAT. Para más "
"información, consulta la <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/transport/ssu "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>documentación en "
"línea</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:620
msgid "Strict Countries"
msgstr "Países Estrictos"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:622
msgid ""
"A list of countries derived from the <a "
"href=https://freedomhouse.org/report/countries-world-freedom-2019 "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>World Freedom "
"Report</a> with a poor civil liberties reputation. This list is used to "
"place routers running in the specified countries in <i>Hidden Mode</i> to "
"provide enhanced security for users. The following countries are designated "
"as strict: Afghanistan, Azerbaijan, Bahrain, Belarus, Brunei, Burundi, "
"Cameroon, Central African Republic, Chad, China, Cuba, Democratic Republic "
"of the Congo, Egypt, Equatorial Guinea, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Iran, Kazakhstan,"
" Laos, Libya, Myanmar, North Korea, Palestinian Territories, Rwanda, Saudi "
"Arabia, Somalia, South Sudan, Sudan, Eswatini (Swaziland), Syria, "
"Tajikistan, Thailand, Turkey, Turkmenistan, Venezuela, United Arab Emirates,"
" Uzbekistan, Western Sahara, Yemen."
msgstr ""
"Una lista de países derivada del <a "
"href=https://freedomhouse.org/report/countries-world-freedom-2019 "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Informe Mundial de "
"Libertad</a> con una mala reputación en cuanto a libertades civiles. Esta "
"lista se usa para colocar enrutadores que funcionan en los países "
"especificados en modo <i>Oculto</i> para proporcionar mayor seguridad a los "
"usuarios. Los siguientes países están designados como estrictos: Afganistán,"
" Azerbaiyán, Baréin, Bielorrusia, Brunéi, Burundi, Camerún, República "
"Centroafricana, Chad, China, Cuba, República Democrática del Congo, Egipto, "
"Guinea Ecuatorial, Eritrea, Etiopía, Irán, Kazajistán, Laos, Libia, "
"Birmania, Corea del Norte, Territorios Palestinos, Ruanda, Arabia Saudita, "
"Somalia, Sudán del Sur, Sudán, Eswatini (Swazilandia), Siria, Tayikistán, "
"Tailandia, Turquía, Turkmenistán, Venezuela, Emiratos Árabes Unidos, "
"Uzbekistán, Sahara Occidental, Yemen."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:624
msgid "Tunnel"
msgstr "Túnel"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:626
msgid ""
"A <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/tunnels/unidirectional class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>unidirectional</a> encrypted "
"communication pathway between a client or server on the I2P network. Similar"
" to a circuit in Tor, except that Tor circuits are bidirectional."
msgstr ""
"Un canal de comunicación cifrado <a "
"href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/tunnels/unidirectional class='sitelink "
"external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>unidireccional</a> entre un cliente o"
" servidor en la red I2P. Similar a un circuito en Tor, excepto que los "
"circuitos de Tor son bidireccionales."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:628
msgid "Tunnel Endpoint"
msgstr "Punto Final del Túnel"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:630
msgid ""
"The last router in a tunnel, which may be the <i>Outbound Endpoint</i>, "
"where the client's tunnels meet the <i>Inbound Gateway</i> of the "
"destination server's tunnels, or the <i>Inbound Endpoint</i> which is the "
"final router in the chain that connects to the destination server."
msgstr ""
"El último enrutador en un túnel, que puede ser el <i>Punto Final de "
"Salida</i>, donde los túneles del cliente se encuentran con el <i>Pasarela "
"de Entrada</i> de los túneles del servidor de destino, o el <i>Punto Final "
"de Entrada</i> que es el enrutador final en la cadena que se conecta al "
"servidor de destino."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:632
msgid "Tunnel Gateway"
msgstr "Pasarela de Túnel"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:634
msgid ""
"The first router in a tunnel. For inbound tunnels, this is the one mentioned"
" in the <i>LeaseSet</i> published in the <i>Network Database</i>. For "
"outbound tunnels, the gateway is the originating router."
msgstr ""
"El primer enrutador en un túnel. Para túneles de entrada, este es el "
"mencionado en el <i>LeaseSet</i> publicado en la <i>Base de Datos de "
"Red</i>. Para túneles de salida, la pasarela es el enrutador de origen."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:638
msgid ""
"A web application supplied with the router that permits creation and "
"configuration of client and server tunnels. Also referred to as the "
"<i>Hidden Services Manager</i>."
msgstr ""
"Una aplicación web suministrada con el enrutador que permite la creación y "
"configuración de túneles cliente y servidor. También se le refiere como el "
"<i>Administrador de Servicios Ocultos</i>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:640
msgid "Tunnel Participant"
msgstr " Participante del Túnel"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:642
msgid "A router in a tunnel not designated as a gateway or endpoint."
msgstr ""
"Un enrutador en un túnel que no está designado como pasarela o punto final."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:644
msgid "ZzzOT (plugin)"
msgstr "ZzzOT (complemento)"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/glossary_jsp.java:646
msgid ""
"A Java I2P plugin implementation of a BitTorrent <a "
"href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opentracker class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Open Tracker</a>. Available from <a "
"href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins "
"class=sitelink>http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins</a>. Source code is available on"
" <a href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.plugins.zzzot class='sitelink external' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un complemento I2P en Java que implementa un rastreador abierto de "
"BitTorrent <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opentracker class='sitelink"
" external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer> Open Tracker</a>. Disponible desde "
"<a href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins "
"class=sitelink>http://stats.i2p/i2p/plugins</a>. Su código fuente está "
"disponible en <a href=https://github.com/i2p/i2p.plugins.zzzot "
"class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>github</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:314
msgid "Web Hosting - I2P+"
msgstr "Alojamiento Web - I2P+"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:470
msgid "Registering an I2P Domain"
msgstr "Registro de un Dominio I2P"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:472
msgid ""
"To obtain your own hostname, I2P domain registrars such as <a "
"href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/addkey.html target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>stats.i2p</a> or <a href=http://reg.i2p/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class=sitelink>reg.i2p</a> provide registration services that"
" allow you to register and manage an .i2p hostname or sub-domain which will "
"then be propagated across the network. Some registration sites will require "
"the <i>B64 destination address</i> for the tunnel/service you wish to "
"associate with a hostname, which you should copy from the <i>Local "
"destination</i> section on the <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/edit?tunnel=3'>Tunnel Manager "
"Configuration page</a>."
msgstr ""
"Para obtener tu propio nombre de host, registradores de dominios I2P como <a"
" href=http://stats.i2p/i2p/addkey.html target=_blank rel=noreferrer "
"class=sitelink>stats.i2p</a> o <a href=http://reg.i2p/ target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer class=sitelink>reg.i2p</a> ofrecen servicios de registro que "
"te permiten registrar y administrar un nombre de host o subdominio .i2p, que"
" luego se propagará en toda la red. Algunos sitios de registro requerirán la"
" dirección de destino <i>B64</i> del túnel/servicio con el que desees "
"asociar un nombre de host, el cual deberías copiar de la sección <i>Destino "
"local</i> en la página de configuración del <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/edit?tunnel=3'>Administrador de "
"Túneles</a>."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:474
msgid ""
"If a <i>Registration Authentication</i> string is requested, you can find it"
" on the <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/register?tunnel=3'>Registration "
"Authentication page</a> linked from the <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/edit?tunnel=3'>Tunnel Manager "
"Configuration page</a>. Registration authentication ensures only the owner "
"is able to register or otherwise manage the hostname, and is required on "
"stats.i2p and reg.i2p."
msgstr ""
"Si se solicita una cadena de <i>Autenticación de Registro</i>, se puede "
"encontrar en la página <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/register?tunnel=3'>Autenticación de "
"Registro</a> enlazada desde la página de configuración del <a "
"href='http://127.0.0.1:7657/i2ptunnel/edit?tunnel=3'>Administrador de "
"Túneles</a>. La autenticación de registro garantiza que solo el propietario "
"pueda registrar o administrar el nombre de host, y es requerida en stats.i2p"
" y reg.i2p."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:476
msgid ""
"If you are in a hurry and can't wait a few hours, you can tell people to use"
" a \"jump\" address helper redirection service. This will usually work "
"within a few minutes of your registering your hostname on the same site. "
"Test it yourself first by entering <code>http://stats.i2p/cgi-"
"bin/jump.cgi?a=<i>yourchosenhostname.i2p</i></code> into your browser. Once "
"it is working, you can tell others to use it."
msgstr ""
"Si estás apurado y no puedes esperar algunas horas, puedes decirle a la "
"gente que use un servicio de redirección de \"salto\" de ayuda de dirección."
" Generalmente funcionará en unos pocos minutos después de registrar tu "
"nombre de host en el mismo sitio. Primero pruébalo tú mismo ingresando "
"<code>http://stats.i2p/cgi-bin/jump.cgi?a=<i>tumismombrdecost.i2p</i></code>"
" en tu navegador. Una vez que funcione, puedes decirles a otros que lo usen."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:478
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can copy the <i>address helper link</i> for your domain, "
"indicated either on the addressbook list page, or on the details page for "
"your domain e.g. <a href='/dns?details&amp;h=skank.i2p&amp;book=router' "
"target=_blank rel=noreferrer>details for skank.i2p</a>, and paste the link "
"where it's required to share it with others."
msgstr ""
"Alternativamente, puede copiar el <i>enlace de ayuda de dirección</i> para "
"su dominio, indicado ya sea en la página de lista de la libreta de "
"direcciones, o en la página de detalles para su dominio p. ej. <a "
"href='/dns?details&amp;h=skank.i2p&amp;book=router' target=_blank "
"rel=noreferrer>detalles para skank.i2p</a>, y pegar el enlace donde se "
"requiera compartirlo con otros."

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:480
msgid "Backup your private key!"
msgstr "¡Haz una copia de respaldo de tu clave privada!"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:482
msgid ""
"When a new service tunnel is created, or a service is run for the first time"
" (e.g. the default jetty webserver, plugins), a private encryption key is "
"created which essentially controls the ownership of address. This is usually"
" named <code>&hellip;privKey.dat</code>, or <code>eepPriv.dat</code>, though"
" it's a good idea to change the name to indicate the service it belongs to "
"and then respecify it in the Tunnel Manager server settings. This .dat file "
"should be backed up safely; lose it and you will lose ownership and control "
"of your hostname!"
msgstr ""
"Cuando se crea un nuevo túnel de servicio o se ejecuta un servicio por "
"primera vez (por ejemplo, el servidor web Jetty predeterminado, "
"complementos), se crea una clave de encriptación privada que controla "
"esencialmente la propiedad de la dirección. Generalmente recibe el nombre "
"<code>&hellip;privKey.dat</code> o <code>eepPriv.dat</code>, aunque es una "
"buena idea cambiar el nombre para indicar el servicio al que pertenece y "
"luego vuelva a especificarlo en la configuración del servidor del "
"Administrador de Túneles. ¡Este archivo .dat debe respaldarse de forma "
"segura; perderlo hará que pierdas la propiedad y el control de tu nombre de "
"host!"

#: /tmp/build-i2p/apps/routerconsole/java/build/../../jsp/WEB-INF/classes/net/i2p/router/web/jsp/help/hostnameregistration_jsp.java:484
msgid ""
"To migrate the key to a new router, or to setup multihoming (running the "
"same service on multiple routers for redundancy and load-balancing), copy "
"the backed up key to your .i2p directory and specify it in the new server "
"tunnel, or replace the default key in the plugin folder (e.g. the zzzot "
"plugin)."
msgstr ""
"Para migrar la clave a un nuevo enrutador o configurar la multipertenencia "
"(ejecutar el mismo servicio en múltiples enrutadores para redundancia y "
"equilibrio de carga), copia la clave de respaldo en tu directorio .i2p y "
"especifícala en el nuevo túnel del servidor, o reemplaza la clave "
"predeterminada en la carpeta del complemento (por ejemplo, el complemento "
"zzzot)."

